BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Wildlife Federation": "https://ncwf.org/event/ayles-creek-planting-burnsville/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_wildlife_federation
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260306T120000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212521
CREATED:20260128T175752Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260203T170348Z
UID:10001450-1772787600-1772798400@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:Ayles Creek Planting (Burnsville)
DESCRIPTION:Join the North Carolina Wildlife Federation and the Southern Appalachian Highlands Conservancy for a livestaking workday at Bowditch Bottoms in Yancey County. Bowditch Bottoms contains a mosaic of habitat types including mixed hardwood forest\, open field\, natural wetland\, and a riparian area that buffers over a half mile of Ayles Creek within the South Toe River Watershed. \nLivestaking is an restoration technique where dormant stem cuttings from trees and shrubs are planted directly into the ground. These cuttings root and grow into new plants. Join us as we plant livestakes along Ayles Creek in areas left bare and susceptible to invasive plant species following Helene. We will plant a variety of native species including ninebark\, silky willow\, elderberry\, and more in an effort to control erosion and enhance habitat for both terrestrial and aquatic wildlife. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/ayles-creek-planting-burnsville/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/bowditchlivestake.jpg
END:VEVENT
