BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/harriet-jacobs-in-the-attic"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive audiovisual experience as we illuminat
 e Harriet Jacobs\, a fugitive North Carolina enslaved person who hid in a t
 iny attic garret for seven years. While hiding she planned her escape\, fle
 d to the North\, and eventually became a key figure in the abolitionist mov
 ement.\n\nIn celebration of Black History Month\, we invite you to explore 
 a to-scale recreation of Harriet’s attic space and listen to readings from 
 her book\, Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl\, which was published in 1
 861.
DTEND:20260307T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260306T140000Z
GEO:39.168209;-86.519998
LOCATION:Malloy/Jordan East Winston Heritage Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Harriet Jacobs in the Attic
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52092289840964
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/harriet-jacobs-in-the-attic
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/steam-over-spencer-a-live-steam-model-train-event"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Special Site Programs
DESCRIPTION:Join us March 5 – 7 for “Steam Over Spencer: A Live Steam Model
  Train Event.” The North Carolina Transportation Museum will be home to sev
 eral large operating model train layouts featuring scale model locomotives 
 that are powered by live steam!\n\nLocomotives and railroad cars in a varie
 ty of scales will be featured during this event\, which is included in regu
 lar museum admission pricing. These locomotives produce their own power fro
 m a variety of fuel sources rather than being powered by an electric curren
 t through the track\, making them different from conventional electric trai
 ns. Owners of these fascinating models are expected to come from across the
  country to share their detailed collections with other hobbyists and museu
 m visitors.\n\nKids and adults alike will enjoy watching these model trains
  in action. While you’re here\, be sure to check out the museum’s exhibits\
 , ride the train (Friday and Saturday only)\, and enjoy the Museum That Mov
 es You!
DTEND:20260306T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260306T140000Z
GEO:35.687243;-80.433348
LOCATION:North Carolina Transportation Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Steam Over Spencer: A Live Steam Model Train Event
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52180987416484
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/steam-over-spencer-a-live-steam-model-
 train-event
END:VEVENT
