X-SOURCE-ID:nc_wildlife_federation
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260307T120000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212521
CREATED:20260302T172222Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T172223Z
UID:10001504-1772877600-1772884800@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:Spring Ephemerals Walk (Raleigh)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF South Wake Conservationists Chapter at Triangle Land Conservancy’s Swift Creek Bluffs Nature Preserve for a spring ephemeral walk. Come along as we embark on a nature walk to discover the many different native spring ephemeral flowers that will be just starting to pop up! The walk will be led by Dr. Eric Pauley\, a local researcher who has conducted plant studies in mountain\, swamp and marine environments\, now with a concentration on Piedmont plants. We will discover the wonders of nature that emerge just in time to announce spring. In addition\, we will learn about the natural history and geography of these unique bluffs and the special microclimate they create. Join us for a spring plant walk! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/spring-ephemerals-walk-raleigh/
CATEGORIES:Featured
END:VEVENT
