SUMMARY:Drafts of the Bull: Durham Craft Beer Tour
DESCRIPTION:Chapel Hill And Durham Fun with Friends (CHAD) 30s 40s 50s+\n*
 *NOTE:** You will need to register for the event on the Flavors of the Bul
 l website. We are holding the date just for our group. Please go to [www.f
 lavorsofthebull.com\,](http://www.flavorsofthebull.com\,/) click the "Book
  now" link in the upper right corner and then search for March 7th.\n\n**U
 se promo code Meetup10 to save 10% off the cost of the tour**.\n\nJoin us 
 for a craft beer tour in downtown Durham! Discover the heart of Durham’s
  craft beer culture with an immersive brewery tour that blends rich flavor
  and local history. Whether you’re a seasoned beer lover or simply curio
 us\, this tour offers an authentic taste of the city—full of character\,
  craftsmanship\, and that unmistakable Durham charm. Cheers to an unforget
 table experience!\n\nThe tour begins at [Clouds Brewing](https://click.c.a
 lumni.umich.edu/?qs=2496befc4dc0a0c62bf4352772a97ad930134646a5ed4de9c969af
 9933bf41ffa0e8316d877e42d862e08c96c84d3643908dfc34dcb896da)\, where they
 ’ve been brewing since 2014 focusing on German-inspired\, American-made 
 bold brews and pub fare. From there\, we’ll head to [Crank Arm Brewing](
 https://click.c.alumni.umich.edu/?qs=2496befc4dc0a0c64e906c9c0b5a717e2464a
 d075c6e17a0e62cccc6af0967f391c3e80975c513078d5bbfb417a040b26bac936a9c2d10a
 4)\, a place that’s been focused on bikes and beer since 2013. The next 
 stop is [Flying Bull Beer Company](https://click.c.alumni.umich.edu/?qs=24
 96befc4dc0a0c6601bd6092f5dc59158eb234652fe945b3c6d0e86479881465ef975cb5351
 d44914f954fda6725c53f6d3961e2d475b13)\, which is focused on building commu
 nity here in Durham through warm hospitality\, great food\, and even bette
 r beer. The last stop is [Atomic Clock Brewing Company](https://click.c.al
 umni.umich.edu/?qs=2496befc4dc0a0c64eaaf0b2b92897f2c1b273b3e03480ef9cde87d
 54ff71d2cd57a36580d5ebbc384249c14dcaaa927f37a1f27f5882ff0)\, known for inn
 ovative brews and a focus on perfection.\n\nThis tour is offered through F
 lavors of the Bull\, a brand-new food and drink tour company in Durham (an
 d started by a Michigan alum). Tours are $75/per person and include flight
 s at each stop\, food tastings throughout the tour\, and local Durham hist
 ory provided as we walk to each stop. Tours are limited to 15 people.\n\nN
 OTE: You will need to register for the event on the Flavors of the Bull we
 bsite. We are holding the date just for our group. Please go to [www.flavo
 rsofthebull.com\,](http://www.flavorsofthebull.com\,/) click the "Book now
 " link in the upper right corner and then search for March 7th.\n\nUse pro
 mo code Meetup10 to to save 10% off the cost of the tour.
