SUMMARY:Art in Bloom Dance Performance
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a special one-time performance in collaboration with the North Carolina Museum of Art\, bringing to life the zodiac theme of Earth. The Panoramic Dance Project\, choreographed by NC State University’s Christa Oliver\, will perform a routine that includes compelling music\, dancers\, and drummers. This is one of four community activations throughout the Triangle region in celebration of NCMA’s upcoming annual fundraiser\, Art in Bloom. \nThe dance performance will be accompanied by a botanical installation on the first floor of the Nature Exploration Center\, inspired by our upcoming special exhibition\, Staying Alive\, created by local floral designer Joseph Barnes.
