X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Wake Audubon": "https://www.wakeaudubon.org/events"}
X-SOURCE-ID:wake_audubon
X-SOURCE:Wake Audubon
URL:https://www.wakeaudubon.org/events
DTSTART:20260307T140000Z
DTEND:20260307T171500Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022522Z
UID:7u13qdbbosg3v4obtgbt5ehb8t@google.com
CREATED:20260212T022215Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>*<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeYgg6Zq9
 HEfnrrOCxiuZ4ejpXddMPoZcG-RKSWGuHGElAACg/viewform?usp=publish-editor" targe
 t="_blank">Complete this form to register.</a> *This free workshop <strong>
 requires registration OFF Meetup.</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>LGBTQ+  Beg
 inner Birders Program with Wake Audubon\, Field Inclusive\, Inc. and Raleig
 h Parks.</strong></p><p><strong>Date: Saturday\, March 7\, 2026</strong></p
 ><p><strong>Time: 9:00* a.m. – 12:15 p.m.</strong> (*Please arrive 15 minut
 es early to reach the Education Center from parking and check-in\; arrive 8
 :40 a.m. if also borrowing binoculars)\,</p><p>Location: <strong>Annie Loui
 se Wilkerson\, MD Nature Preserve Park</strong>\, 5229 Awls Haven Dr.\, Ral
 eigh\, NC 27614</p><p></p><p>Hosting this event expressly for the LGBTQ+ co
 mmunity are workshop sponsors <a href="https://wakeaudubon.org/" target="_b
 lank">Wake Audubon</a> and <a href="https://www.fieldinclusive.org/" target
 ="_blank">Field Inclusive\, Inc.</a> in partnership with <a href="https://r
 aleighnc.gov/parks" target="_blank">City of Raleigh Parks</a> and the <a hr
 ef="https://www.lgbtcenterofraleigh.com/" target="_blank">LGBT Center of Ra
 leigh</a>. Collectively we’re striving for everyone to feel welcome\, safe 
 and included in the natural sciences and outdoors.</p><p></p><p>‘Birding’ –
  or the observation of birds in their natural habitats as a hobby – has bec
 ome one of the most popular outdoor activities. If you are taking a new int
 erest in birds and looking for help getting started\, come develop your ski
 lls together with others at our Beginning Birding workshop.</p><p></p><p>Th
 is free public program teaches the basics of bird identification\; how to u
 se binoculars\, guides and apps\; types of bird safety and ways to bird saf
 ely\; and the importance of inclusion and allyship in birding and the outdo
 ors. We’ll spend time outside putting your learning to quick use.</p><p></p
 ><p>Our route outside will consist of a mix of paved\, gravel\, and grassy 
 surfaces with slight gradients. All-gendered restrooms will be available.</
 p><p></p><p>No binoculars? No problem! We have plenty of loaners to spare.<
 /p><p></p><p><strong>Note: Participation may be capped due to space restric
 tions</strong>\, at which time <strong>notice of a wait list will be added 
 to the top of the registration form</strong>. Please continue to register t
 o join the waitlist. Should we receive cancellations\, we’ll right away inv
 ite those on waitlist to confirm in the order registrations were received.<
 /p><p></p><p>Reach Wake Audubon board director and Equity\, Diversity\, Inc
 lusion and Belonging co-chair Rick LaRose at <a href="mailto:rlarose.was@gm
 ail.com" target="_blank">rlarose.was@gmail.com</a> with any questions.</p><
 p></p><p>We look forward to building your beginner birding skills together 
 with you on March 7!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T022442Z
LOCATION:Annie Louise Wilkerson\, MD Nature Preserve Park\, 5229 Awls Haven
  Dr\, Raleigh\, NC 27614\, USA
SEQUENCE:1
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:LGBTQ+ Beginner Bird 
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
