DESCRIPTION:Sauthier Map Walking Tour - explore the town as it was in 1770.
  11:30 a.m. and 1:30 p.m. Starts at Exhibit Center. Costumed interpreters.S
 tory of the First Port and Post Road – first of five customs collections di
 stricts and designated sites for royal customs collection. Exhibit Center. 
 Story of the 1734 St. Thomas Church and their library\, the first in the st
 ate. from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. there will be a guide at St. Thomas to tell its
  history\, and the church Gift Shop will be open (101 Craven St.)      Find
  out how Genealogy can not only help tell the story of your family\, but ho
 w you can find out about those living hundreds of years ago. From 10 a.m. -
  12:30 a.m. local genealogists will be here to answer your questions. Exhib
 it Center Spinning and weaving will be demonstrated on the porch of the Van
 DerVeer House. Costumed interpreters.Munitions Firing Demonstrations will t
 ake place at about 11 a.m.\, 1 p.m.\, and 2 p.m. in the VanDerVeer yard (10
 5 S. Harding Street) Costumed interpreters.
DTEND:20260307T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
