BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/boomtown-bash"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:Step back in time to the bustling 1850s with Reed Gold Mine’s n
 ew immersive living history event\, "Boomtown Bash: Life at a Carolina Gold
  Mine." Focused on the heyday of North Carolina’s gold mining history\, thi
 s event offers a captivating look into the lives of the miners\, immigrants
 \, and women who sought adventure and riches.\n\nThe outdoor Panning Area a
 lso be open for the event (weather permitting)! After learning about gold m
 ining in the 19th century\, try your hand at panning in our troughs and see
  if you have what it takes to strike it rich yourself. Panning tickets are 
 $5.00 each\, plus tax\, for anyone ages 8 and older. Tickets are sold for s
 et session times on a first come\, first served basis in our Visitor Center
 .\n\nVisitors of all ages will enjoy an unforgettable experience at “Boomto
 wn Bash” by being transported back in time to the 1850s and reliving the sp
 irit of adventure and pursuit of wealth that defined North Carolina’s Piedm
 ont region until the dawn of the Civil War. Don’t miss your chance to learn
  more about America’s first Golden State and discover the forgotten history
  of North Carolina’s gold mining heritage.\n\n“Boomtown Bash” will be held 
 from 10:00 am to 4:00 pm on Saturday\, March 7th.\n\nEvent admission is $5.
 00 for anyone aged 5 and up\, payable on the event day. We accept cash and 
 cards\, excluding American Express. Children under 5 are free. Registration
  is not accepted.
DTEND:20260307T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260307T150000Z
GEO:35.285531;-80.466459
LOCATION:Reed Gold Mine
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Canceled: Boomtown Bash 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51764758013897
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/boomtown-bash
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/kinstons-civil-war-experience-homefront-sailors-and-soldiers"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Special Site Programs,Education Programs,Youth 
 & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:🤔🏛️ Curious about Kinston during the Civil War? \n\nAre you cur
 ious about the businesses that operated in downtown Kinston during the Civi
 l War? Did you know Kinston was home to a Free Black community during this 
 pivotal time? Ever wondered what daily life was like for women and children
  while men were away at war?\n\n🪖💭 Were any battles fought in Kinston?\n⚓ D
 o you know where the CSS Neuse ironclad was outfitted—and who served aboard
  her?\n📜 What were the two largest Civil War battles fought in North Caroli
 na?\n\nIf these questions spark your interest\, join us for a day of explor
 ation into Lenoir County’s history during the 1860s!\n\nThroughout the muse
 um\, our knowledgeable staff and volunteers will bring history to life with
  living history demonstrations\, interactive discussions\, and helpful reso
 urces—all designed to answer your questions and deepen your understanding o
 f life in North Carolina during the Civil War.\n\n🎖️👩‍👩‍👦‍👦⚓\nPerfect for f
 amilies\, history enthusiasts\, and curious minds of all ages—this event of
 fers a meaningful and memorable way to connect with the past.\n\nExplore\, 
 learn\, and experience history where it happened. We can’t wait to welcome 
 you!\n\n🎟️ Admission Rates:\n\n$5 – Adults$4 – Senior Citizens\, Active Dut
 y Military\, and Veterans$3 – StudentsFree – Children ages three and under📧
