DESCRIPTION:Become a FrogWatch USA volunteer with the NC Aquariums Chapter.
  The 2-day volunteer training\, hosted by Battleship North Carolina is bein
 g offered on March 8 (10:00 a.m. - 4:00 p.m.) and on March 15 (1:00 p.m. - 
 4:00 p.m.). Become a FrogWatch USA community scientist by attending both da
 tes. \n\nFrogWatch USA volunteers learn to identify frogs and toads by thei
 r breeding calls. Each 2-day training introduces FrogWatch protocols and pr
 ocedures\, introduces the breeding calls of local species\, and provides a 
 mock listening sessions for practice. Volunteers who complete the training 
 are invited to engage in social listening sessions throughout southeast NC 
 and receive a quarterly newsletter regarding FrogWatch activity.\n\n(To reg
 ister or to see other training dates/locations\, please visit the NC Aquari
 um at Fort Fisher website at the link provided. For more information about 
 FrogWatch USA and becoming a volunteer\, please email Kristin.Holloman-Noe@
 ncaquariums.com.
