DESCRIPTION:Please join Engaged Defenders for Democracy on Mondays from 4:3
 0-6pm at the corner of Franklin St &amp\; Elliott Rd in Chapel Hill for a w
 eekly\, peaceful\, nonpartisan protest and call to action. Free parking at 
 the Church of Reconciliation\, 110 N Elliott Rd.\n\nAcross the political sp
 ectrum\, Americans are disillusioned by leaders who put power over people. 
 We gather to build community\, spark hope\, and inspire action.\n\nBring a 
 friend. Bring a sign. Speak up for immigrant rights\, free speech\, healthc
 are\, social security\, the environment\, the Constitution and the rule of 
 law\, reproductive freedom\, job and funding cuts\, and the many\, many oth
 er issues close to our hearts. Bonus points for signs that encourage others
  to move beyond honking and help turn awareness into action. \nWe often han
 d out fliers to stopped cars &amp\; pedestrians with information about rele
 vant actions folks can take to support their community and defend democracy
 . We also have a Signal chat for regular attenders. If you are interested i
 n either of these opportunities\, ask around for Wendy.\n---------\nTIME\nS
 tarting Monday March 9th\, will switch to 4:30-6 pm - Nov 2. Then will swit
 ch back to 3:30-5 pm.\n\nThis will be a POSITIVE and nonviolent demonstrati
 on. We are here to protect our democracy. We are standing up for what we be
 lieve in. We want to inspire people to join us and grow our movement!\n\nPl
 ease bring positive signs supporting the movement and resisting what is hap
 pening in our country!\n\nPlease no mocking signs\, no swastikas\n\nWe are 
 excited to see you there and stand together for our country!\n\nSee you eve
 ry Monday afternoon engaging drivers in Chapel Hill!\n\nPlease join our Sub
 stack: <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://substack.com/profile/1
 15484101-engaged-defenders-4-democracy&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;
 usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw3y7Kv9RwiMPWcPPUFQih9k" target="_blank">https://substa
 ck.com/profile/115484101-engaged-defenders-4-democracy</a>\n\nFor more ED4D
  Mobilize Events: <a href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.mobiliz
 e.us/engagedefendersfordemocracy/&amp\;sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2
 &amp\;usg=AOvVaw1xqNbFip0P6DfK4plFB1D7" target="_blank">https://www.mobiliz
 e.us/engagedefendersfordemocracy/</a>\n\n<a href="https://www.google.com/ur
 l?q=https://www.mobilize.us/engagedefendersfordemocracy/event/881592/&amp\;
 sa=D&amp\;source=calendar&amp\;usd=2&amp\;usg=AOvVaw2ha5lmqlktFCNfNoKhhOC5"
  target="_blank">https://www.mobilize.us/engagedefendersfordemocracy/event/
 881592/</a>
