CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks,Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Solving Sustainability is a live interdisciplinary podcast that
  seeks to raise awareness about macro-level sustainability challenges and i
 nnovations while fostering meaningful discussion between students\, researc
 hers\, entrepreneurs and policymakers.\n\nThe third episode of the podcast\
 , "Future Sources of Protein\," will delve into the scientific innovations\
 , environmental trade-offs and economic considerations shaping alternative 
 protein systems. The discussion will focus on plant-based foods\, precision
  fermentation and cultivated meat and how they will shape the future of sus
 tainable food production. The guests on the podcast will be: \n\nRohan Shir
 waiker\, co-director of the Bezos CenterRody Hawkins\, CEO of Improved Natu
 reAjinkya Arun Atkare\, co-president of the Alt Protein Project at NC State
