X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive audiovisual experience as we illuminat
 e Harriet Jacobs\, a fugitive North Carolina enslaved person who hid in a t
 iny attic garret for seven years. While hiding she planned her escape\, fle
 d to the North\, and eventually became a key figure in the abolitionist mov
 ement.\n\nIn celebration of Black History Month\, we invite you to explore 
 a to-scale recreation of Harriet’s attic space and listen to readings from 
 her book\, Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl\, which was published in 1
 861.
DTEND:20260311T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
