X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Want to tell a story using images\, videos\, documents\, or oth
 er media from your research project? You can create and host a digital exhi
 bit fore free using CollectionBuilder! This workshop will cover how to set 
 up your own digital exhibit using CollectionBuilder and Google Sheets. Atte
 ndees will learn how to add images\, PDFs\, videos\, and more to their webs
 ite. CollectionBuilder makes it easy to set up your own digital exhibit wit
 h minimal technical expertise.\n\n \n\nThis workshop is offered by the Univ
 ersity Libraries and will be led by librarian Rolando Rodriguez and CALA Sh
 annon Henry. \n\n \n\nThis workshop is being offered remotely via Zoom only
 . Registrants will receive a Zoom link\; those on the waitlist will not rec
 eive a Zoom link unless they are bumped up to a registered spot. After the 
 workshop\, registrants and those on the waitlist will receive a link to the
  workshop recording. You can register on the University Libraries calendar:
  https://calendar.lib.unc.edu/event/16023378
DTEND:20260310T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022131Z
DTSTART:20260310T170000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Creating Your Own Digital Exhibit
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51630398262621
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/creating-your-own-digital-exhibit
END:VEVENT
