SUMMARY:Fiddleheads: Preschool Nature Explorers - Spring
DESCRIPTION:Register Here\n\nAges: 4-5\nDate: Wednesdays\, March 11 – April 22 (6-week series; no class on April 1)\nTime: 1:30 – 4:00 PM\nLocation: North Carolina Botanical Garden\nFee: $180 ($162 Household & above Members) \n  \nLet curiosity lead the way! In this playful\, nature-based drop-off program\, preschoolers will discover the wonders of spring through hands-on activities\, outdoor adventures\, seasonal crafts\, storytelling\, and group play. Led by Garden environmental educators\, each week explores a new theme—like frogs singing in the ponds\, spring wildflowers\, and busy pollinators —designed to foster joyful connection with the natural world. \nThis is a 6-week program that meets once a week on Wednesdays (except 4/1). Each session starts in the children’s classroom before we head outdoors to explore nature’s classroom—our native plant gardens and forest trails! A healthy snack is included. Group limited to 10. \n  \nRegister Here
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/fiddleheads-preschool-nature-explorers-spring/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Learn
GEO:35.901081;-79.031939
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=North Carolina Botanical Garden 100 Old Mason Farm Road Chapel Hill NC 27517 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=100 Old Mason Farm Road:geo:-79.031939,35.901081
END:VEVENT
