X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:Have you ever felt tired and sluggish at work? Do you notice te
 nsion in your neck and back pain in the middle of your workday? Spending ma
 ny of our waking hours sitting at a desk can lead to consequences for our h
 ealth. However\, it can be difficult to find time to exercise! This trainin
 g will discuss the importance of not being completely sedentary all day\, a
 nd review practical\, easy ways to take care of your body while working a d
 esk job.\n\n \n\nWorkshop Objectives:\n\nThis training will help you:\n• Le
 arn why sedentary lifestyles are hazardous for your health\n• Identify exer
 cises to incorporate into your workday\n• Understand the relationship betwe
 en physical and mental stress\n• Practice mind-body connection through stre
 ss management exercises\n\n \n\nClick on Carolina Talent registration link 
 and select the “Request” button to automatically enroll.
DTEND:20260311T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022131Z
DTSTART:20260311T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
