X-SOURCE-URLS:{"United Arts Wake": "https://unitedarts.org/calendar/the-road-through-dont-ask-dont-tell/2026-03-12/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:united_arts_wake
X-SOURCE:United Arts Wake
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T220000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212541
CREATED:20260120T155524Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260120T155524Z
UID:10006489-1773306000-1773352800@unitedarts.org
SUMMARY:The Road Through “Don’t Ask\, Don’t Tell”
DESCRIPTION:The Road Through Don’t Ask\, Don’t Tell by photographer\, oral historian\, and U.S. Marine Corps veteran Theresa Scott. This deeply personal documentary exhibition explores the lived experiences of LGBTQIA+ veterans who served under restrictive military policies. \nThrough intimate portrait photography paired with first-person oral histories\, Scott brings forward stories long silenced by institutional policy and cultural pressure. Drawing on her own service\, she offers viewers an unflinching look at the realities faced by service members who were expected to serve with honor while hiding essential parts of who they were. \nExhibition Dates: February 1 – April 26\, 2026\nArtist Talk & Reception: March 26\, 5:30–7:00 p.m.
URL:https://unitedarts.org/calendar/the-road-through-dont-ask-dont-tell/2026-03-12/
LOCATION:Pullen Arts Center
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://unitedarts.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/DADT-24.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Pullen Arts Center":MAILTO:pullenartscenter@raleighnc.gov
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Botanical Garden": "https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/drawing-and-understanding-conifer-trees-in-micron-pen/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_botanical_garden
X-SOURCE:NC Botanical Garden
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T153000
DTSTAMP:20260306T165851
CREATED:20260108T152919Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260120T194633Z
UID:10000827-1773307800-1773329400@ncbg.unc.edu
SUMMARY:Drawing and Understanding Conifer Trees in Micron Pen
DESCRIPTION:Register Here\n\nwith Stacy-Ann Searle\, Landscape Artist \nDate: Thursday\, March 12\, 2026\nTime: 9:30 a.m. – 3:30 p.m.\nLocation: North Carolina Botanical Garden\nFee: $78 ($70 Members) \n  \nConifers come in many varieties. In this three-session workshop\, we will explore how to capture the different overarching structure of these trees\, as well as a variety of leaf/needle forms and bark textures. For this class\, we will be using micron pens to create a variety of small ink studies. Students will gain an understanding of the different mark making techniques\, how to create textures in ink and gain confidence in using this very approachable ink medium. \n  \nRegister Here
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/drawing-and-understanding-conifer-trees-in-micron-pen/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Learn
GEO:35.901081;-79.031939
