GEO:35.7595731;-79.0192997
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/copy-of-ai-hot-topics-at-nc-state-3260"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:The AI Hot Topics monthly networking series is a dynamic forum 
 designed to foster dialogue and collaboration around the rapidly evolving a
 rtificial intelligence field. Whether you’re a seasoned AI practitioner\, a
  curious scholar\, or simply interested in the transformative potential of 
 AI\, this series offers a unique opportunity to connect with leading expert
 s and contribute to meaningful discussions.\n\nDate: March 12\, 2026\n\nTit
 le: Beyond Prediction: Synthetic Data\, Agentic Intelligence\, and Quantum 
 Acceleration.\n\nDescription: This session highlights three emerging AI tre
 nds shaping safer and more capable systems. It covers how synthetic data an
 d digital twins enable secure\, controlled experimentation\; how agentic AI
  allows systems to observe\, reason\, and act within set boundaries\; and w
 hen quantum-supported optimization can offer real benefits. Participants wi
 ll gain a clear view of how these developments work together to support res
 ponsible\, scalable decision-making across research and industry.\n\nModera
 tor: Carlos Pinheiro\,  Distinguished Data Scientist\, SAS\n\nPanelists: \n
 \nUdo Sglavo\, Vice President\, Applied AI and Modeling R&D\, SAS\n\nHardi 
 Desai\, Senior Data Scientist\, Applied AI & Machine Learning\, SAS \n\nMun
 indar Singh\, SAS Institute Distinguished Professor of Computer Science\, N
 C State University
DTEND:20260312T134500Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022450Z
DTSTART:20260312T124500Z
GEO:35.771067;-78.676515
LOCATION:Partners I – NC State University\, Raleigh Founded (Suite 1650)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:AI Hot Topics at NC State
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51253444447648
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/copy-of-ai-hot-topics-at-nc-state-3260
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/harriet-jacobs-in-the-attic"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an immersive audiovisual experience as we illuminat
 e Harriet Jacobs\, a fugitive North Carolina enslaved person who hid in a t
 iny attic garret for seven years. While hiding she planned her escape\, fle
 d to the North\, and eventually became a key figure in the abolitionist mov
 ement.\n\nIn celebration of Black History Month\, we invite you to explore 
 a to-scale recreation of Harriet’s attic space and listen to readings from 
 her book\, Incidents in the Life of a Slave Girl\, which was published in 1
 861.
DTEND:20260313T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260312T130000Z
GEO:39.168209;-86.519998
LOCATION:Malloy/Jordan East Winston Heritage Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Harriet Jacobs in the Attic
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52092289844040
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/harriet-jacobs-in-the-attic
END:VEVENT
