BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Wildlife Federation": "https://ncwf.org/event/a-hikers-journey-on-the-pacific-crest-trail-greensboro/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_wildlife_federation
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T193000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212521
CREATED:20260128T181057Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T161713Z
UID:10001453-1773338400-1773343800@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:A Hiker's Journey on the Pacific Crest Trail (Greensboro)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Triad Wild! Chapter and REI as they welcome NCWF Conservation Coordinator\, Luke Bennett. In 2024\, Luke decided to run away from responsibilities and thru-hike the 2\,650 mile Pacific Crest Trail heading Southbound from Canada to Mexico. Along the way he experienced stunning landscapes\, close encounters with wildlife (including a near death experience with a grouse)\, and approximately 10 million blisters. Beyond a walk in the woods\, the PCT brought to light the importance of prioritizing time outside with friends and family\, the necessity to protect public lands\, the overwhelming kindness of strangers\, the subtle art of hitchhiking\, the struggle of being away from home\, and the beauty of a properly topped bowl of oatmeal. Join us with your favorite trail snack as we pack an adventure of a lifetime into one hour! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/a-hikers-journey-on-the-pacific-crest-trail-greensboro/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/trail.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Transitions LifeCare": "https://www.transitionslifecare.org/event/nurturing-nests-a-family-workshop/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:transitions_lifecare
X-SOURCE:Transitions LifeCare
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260312T200000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212520
CREATED:20251218T191813Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251218T191813Z
UID:10002533-1773338400-1773345600@www.transitionslifecare.org
SUMMARY:Nurturing Nests: A Family Workshop
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a family fun night\, where families of all ages\, shapes\, sizes\, and relationships are welcome. This workshop is an opportunity to come together\, support one another\, and create a lasting tribute to your loved one. Through the act of decorating a birdhouse\, you’ll work together to create a tangible reminder of your connection to your loved one. This workshop is a safe\, welcoming space to connect\, reflect\, and commemorate your journey through grief together. Come prepared to get a little messy. All supplies are provided (one bird house per family unit). Participants are invited to bring memory items (buttons\, jewelry\, pieces of clothing\, etc.) to include in the decoration of their birdhouse. \nRegistration is limited\, please call 919-719-7199 to reserve your space. \nDrop-in pizza dinner at 5:30pm
URL:https://www.transitionslifecare.org/event/nurturing-nests-a-family-workshop/
LOCATION:Transitions LifeCare\, 250 Hospice Circle\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
CATEGORIES:Grief Support,Grief Support for Adults
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.transitionslifecare.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Birdhouse-Spring-scaled-e1704987358928.jpg
GEO:35.8074456;-78.7418081
