DESCRIPTION:Down Home NC\n \nJoin families across Durham who are building a
  movement to fight for fully funded\, welcoming public schools. Share a mea
 l\, hear from other families\, build community\, and learn how we can win r
 eal change together.\n\nAre you frustrated with what's happening in Durham 
 public schools? You're not alone.\n\nParents and caregivers from schools ac
 ross Durham are coming together to build the power we need to fight back. A
 t this gathering\, you'll:\n\n→ Connect with other families who share your 
 concerns \n→ Hear stories from parents organizing at their schools \n→ Lear
 n about the real forces behind the cuts and chaos—and what YOU can do about
  it \n→ Leave with a clear next step to get involved\n\nChildcare and dinne
 r provided. Bring someone with you—a neighbor\, a friend\, a co-worker\, an
 other parent from your school!\n\nThis is for anyone who cares about public
  education: parents\, grandparents\, aunts\, uncles\, and community members
  connected to public schools.\n\nQuestions? Contact Courtney at Courtney@ca
 rolinafederation.org.\n\nhttps://www.mobilize.us/carolinafederation/event/8
 78601/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T225910Z
LOCATION:Holton Career & Resource Center (2nd Floor\, Room 2120)\, 401 N Dr
 iver St\, Durham\, NC 27703\, Durham\, NC\, 27705
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Our Schools\, Our Future: Durham Public School Family Gathering
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/andrews-launch-accelerator-launch-sessions"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training
DESCRIPTION:The Andrews Launch Accelerator's Launch Sessions are designed t
 o help ventures articulate\, validate and communicate their value to key pr
 ograms and stakeholders. The schedule for the Launch Sessions is below. All
  sessions will be held virtually.\n\nSession 1 (Feb. 26): Join us for an in
 troduction to the Andrews Launch Accelerator\, the Launch Sessions and the 
 first core principle: customer discovery.\n\nSession 2 ( March 5): This ses
 sion will explore the often-overlooked fundamentals of customer discovery. 
  It will focus heavily on understanding your customers' frustrations\, diss
 atisfactions and unfulfilled desires. The session will also delve into coll
 ecting evidence of these things through unbiased discovery work.\n\nSession
  3 (March 12): You'll learn about the methods entrepreneurs use to rapidly 
 validate demand for what they are working on without spending a lot of mone
 y and time.\n\nSession 4 (March 26): With just a few days left before the A
 ndrews Launch Accelerator applications are due on March 31\, this session w
 ill be an open-floor Q&A on anything related to the Andrews Launch Accelera
 tor\, including applications.
DTEND:20260312T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022450Z
DTSTART:20260312T220000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Andrews Launch Accelerator: Launch Sessions
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51939174094233
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/andrews-launch-accelerator-launch-sessi
 ons
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/femtech-panel-showcase"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Join the NC State University Libraries for a celebration of the
  work of NC State faculty and alumni whose design practices have led them i
 nto the femtech industry. This event will highlight how human-centered desi
 gn and emerging technologies are being applied to menstrual care\, pelvic h
 ealth\, post-mastectomy support and overall well-being. Speakers will offer
  short lightning talks on their projects\, followed by a panel discussion m
 oderated by Kelly Umstead\, associate professor of industrial design. Atten
 dees will also have the opportunity to view prototypes and engage directly 
 with the designers behind the work.\n\nThe panelists are:\n\n• Paula León i
 s an industrial design graduate and medical device designer whose work with
  Blean reimagines menstrual cup care through inclusive\, sustainable design
  to make hygiene easier and more empowering.\n• Jabria Oliver is a recent N
 C State Master of Industrial Design graduate and founder of Off the Rag\, a
  mission-driven initiative eliminating period poverty with innovative menst
 rual care solutions that protect dignity and basic needs.\n• Abby Scheer is
  a designer who led the early design and development of Cervu Health\, an i
 nnovative pelvic health system created through human-centered design and cl
 inical insight.\n• Yuanqing “Ching” Tian\, Ph.D.\, is an assistant professo
 r of industrial design whose research focuses on custom-fit wearable produc
 t design using 3D scanning\, parametric design and digital fabrication to e
 nhance well-being.\n• Kelly Umstead is an associate professor of industrial
  design at NC State University whose work focuses on human-centered design\
 , health and well-being and mentoring students translating design research 
 into real-world impact.
DTEND:20260312T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022450Z
DTSTART:20260312T220000Z
GEO:35.769292;-78.676638
LOCATION:James B. Hunt Jr. Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:FemTech Panel and Showcase
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51830849191975
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/femtech-panel-showcase
END:VEVENT
