SUMMARY:Orange County Wildlife Habitat Stewards Training (Hillsborough)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF and NCWF Tri-County Conservationists Chapter for three fun-filled days of renowned speakers and hands-on activities at the Orange County Cooperative Extension Office in Hillsborough! Come participate in NCWF’s Wildlife Habitat Steward Training program and become a certified wildlife habitat steward. This program will allow participants to increase their knowledge and ability to protect\, conserve\, and restore habitat for local wildlife. Participants will also have the opportunity to engage with experts and fellow conservation enthusiasts about a variety of wildlife topics. Application is required and due by February 25th. \nTHIS EVENT IS NOW FULL. STAY TUNED FOR FUTURE WILDLIFE HABITAT STEWARDS TRAINING EVENTS.
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/wildlife-habitat-stewards-training-hillsborough/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/OrangeWHST.jpg
END:VEVENT
