BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: All Things AI": "https://www.meetup.com/all-things-ai-live/events/313624941/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_all_things_ai
X-SOURCE:Meetup: All Things AI
UID:event_313624941@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260307T022535Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T113000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260313T143000
SUMMARY:AI Friday Forum
DESCRIPTION:All Things AI (Live)\nNormally we don't promote other events o
 n the All Things AI meetup group but on March 13th\, Our co-founder\, Mark
  Hinkle is presenting at the MarketingProfs Friday Forum.\n\nAlso [Pam Did
 ner](https://pamdidner.com)\, has been a supporter of All Things AI and pa
 id for the refreshments at our last Meetup. So it's really sort of a meetu
 p of our ATAI folks too.\n\nIt's a good opprtunity for marketers and virtu
 ally anyone else to learn how to use AI in their workflows.\n\n#### From P
 rompts to Knowledge: Laying the Foundation for Agentic Marketing Workflows
 \n\n**TIME:** 11:30am–12:15pm\n**LENGTH:** 45 minutes\nMost AI prompts t
 oday are written in isolation—one question\, one output\, one-off result
 s.\n\nBut scalable AI work doesn't start with better prompts. It starts wi
 th compartmentalizing your domain knowledge in a way AI can understand: cl
 ear intent\, boundaries\, inputs\, outputs\, and decision logic.\n\nIn thi
 s session\, Pam Didner walks you through the next level of AI skills\, sho
 wing you how to use agents for specific tasks to create a team of virtual 
 assistants working together for YOU!\n\n**Join Pam to discover how to:**\n
 \n* Move from ad-hoc prompts to personal and team knowledge\n* Structure y
 our expertise so AI can parse\, understand\, and reuse it\n* Create a back
 bone structured knowledge for custom AI agents—and eventually workflows\
 n\n***\n\n**SPEAKER**\n\n**Pam Didner - B2B Marketer\, Speaker\, Author\, 
 & Podcaster**\nPam understands the challenges business professionals face 
 every day. She loves to be in the trenches with her clients to solve their
  problems and grow their businesses. With 20 years of corporate experience
  across many departments and industries\, she knows how corporate works.\n
 \n#### Reproducible Marketing Workflows That Actually Work\n\n**TIME:** 1:
 15pm–2pm\n**LENGTH:** 45 minutes\n\nEveryone's chasing the perfect promp
 t. But that's not where the leverage is. The marketers getting real result
 s from AI aren't prompt engineers—they're workflow architects. They've l
 earned to dissect their work into discrete tasks\, then strategically sort
  which belong to humans and which belong to AI.\n\nIn this session\, Mark 
 Hinkle will apply his S.M.A.R.T. framework (Sort\, Match\, Automate\, Refi
 ne\, Take Control) for newsletter production as a working example\, breaki
 ng it down step-by-step: research\, ideation\, writing\, editing\, distrib
 ution.\n\nYou'll see exactly where AI accelerates the process\, where huma
 ns remain irreplaceable\, and how to design the handoffs that make or brea
 k your output quality.\n\n**You'll learn:**\n\n* Where AI can be used—an
 d where it should not be used—in your marketing\n* A methodology you can
  apply Monday morning to email campaigns\, social content\, blog productio
 n\, or any content workflow in your stack\n* The S.M.A.R.T. framework that
  delivers consistent results from AI\n\n***\n\n**SPEAKER**\nMark Hinkle\, 
 is the co-founder of All Things AI.\nMark Hinkle is a veteran of the enter
 prise software industry and founder of Peripety Labs. With expertise spann
 ing the internet\, open source software\, cloud computing\, systems manage
 ment\, and artificial intelligence\, he helps organizations deploy product
 ion-grade AI solutions. He created the Artificially Intelligent Operating 
 System (AIOS) to train professionals across roles\, and publishes The Arti
 ficially Intelligent Enterprise\, a newsletter with over 250\,000 subscrib
 ers. Mark leads the 3\,000+ member All Things AI Meetup in Raleigh-Durham\
 , part of the broader All Things AI community\, which hosts free monthly e
 vents and conferences.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/all-things-ai-live/events/313624941/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260303T234748Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260303T234748Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
