SUMMARY:Spring Ephemerals
DESCRIPTION:North Carolina is home to many types of amazing plants. Some are “spring ephemerals\,” small plants that go through their entire lifecycle in a very short amount of time right as spring begins. Come learn about Bloodroot\, Trout Lily\, and many more! \nThis virtual program is especially for kids in grades K-8\, but everyone is welcome.  You do not need to join ecoEXPLORE before the program\, but should you choose to create an account for your child so they can get started documenting wildlife for scientists and earning prizes\, visit ecoexplore.net. \nRegister here
