X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/1776-the-musical"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Concerts (Music),Theater & Musicals
DESCRIPTION:Experience the birth of a nation like never before in 1776 the 
 Musical\, a bold and witty retelling of America’s fight for independence. A
 s tensions rise in the Second Continental Congress\, John Adams\, Thomas Je
 fferson\, and Benjamin Franklin struggle to persuade a divided nation to de
 clare freedom from British rule. With a Tony Award-winning score and a fres
 h\, thought-provoking perspective\, this powerful production brings history
  to life with humor\, heart\, and relevance for today. Thalian Hall is prou
 d to co-produce this with Thalian Association for our 25-26 season.\n\nDon’
 t miss this rousing journey to the signing of the Declaration of Independen
 ce!
DTEND:20260314T020000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260313T233000Z
GEO:34.237179;-77.945805
