 l\, NC<br>Leader: Frank D<br>This birdwalk repeats on the second Saturday o
 f most months. Check Meetup ( <a href="https://www.meetup.com/wake-audubon-
 meetup/" target="_blank">https://www.meetup.com/wake-audubon-meetup/</a> ) 
 and <a href="http://wakeaudubon.org" target="_blank">wakeaudubon.org</a> ca
 lendars for updates.<br><br>Wendell Park is one of our easternmost Wake Cou
 nty hotspots. It has a range of habitats. It tends to get plenty of winter 
 birds if conditions are right (not windy). <br><br>Technically\, an RSVP is
  not required for this birdwalk\, but it is helpful. <br><br>Park in the gr
 assy field on the left. Look for people with binoculars.<br><br>Wendell Par
 k ebird hotspot: <a href="http://ebird.org/ebird/hotspot/L5460345" target="
 _blank">http://ebird.org/ebird/hotspot/L5460345</a><br><br>Thank you for yo
 ur interest in birding with others. Our Meetup is FREE to you and supported
