CREATED:20260212T053528Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T053528Z
UID:119314-1773493200-1773500400@naturalsciences.org
SUMMARY:Learning From Lichens
DESCRIPTION:Explore the beautiful and mysterious world of lichens! Join us for a walk through the bottomlands of Prairie Ridge as we look for lichens\, learn to identify them\, and contribute lichen observations to the global collaborative science project iNaturalist. We will learn about lichen ecology\, biology\, and how they are crucial kin. \nThis program is for ages 8+. Meet in the Outdoor Classroom\, a 3-5 minute walk down the gravel path from the parking lot. From there we will take a leisurely stroll down to the creek\, about a quarter mile. Bring water\, a notebook if you’d like\, and dress for the weather.
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/learning-from-lichens/
LOCATION:Prairie Ridge\, 1671 Gold Star Drive\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27607\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adults,Children,Citizen Science,Educators,K-12 Students,Outdoor Experiences,Walk-up Programs
ORGANIZER;CN="Lucie%20Ciccone":MAILTO:lucie.ciccone@naturalsciences.org
GEO:35.812182885871;-78.713963528554
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Prairie Ridge 1671 Gold Star Drive Raleigh NC 27607 United States;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=1671 Gold Star Drive:geo:-78.713963528554,35.812182885871
END:VEVENT
