DTSTART:20260314T130000Z
DTEND:20260314T161500Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022522Z
UID:64fakkhl92ohkgcmdga4b3aj5k@google.com
CREATED:20260212T022508Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>*<a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSe_PhB01W
 HQRiDCzz4btZ-eCcox1v_9ek22zCaWHy-oNc2seQ/viewform?usp=publish-editor">Compl
 ete this form to register</a><a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FA
 IpQLSdBiAmkILZmcX03xqoBbOa01hQvNzq6agG66PbJmWRXqbWlSA/viewform?usp=dialog">
 .</a> *This free workshop <strong>requires registration OFF Meetup.</strong
 ></p><p><strong>Beginner Birders Program with Wake Audubon and Raleigh Park
 s.</strong></p><p><strong>Date: Saturday\, March 14\, 2026</strong></p><p><
 strong>Time: 9:00* a.m. – 12:15 p.m.</strong> (*Please arrive 10 minutes ea
 rly to check in\; arrive 8:40 a.m. if borrowing binoculars)\,</p><p><strong
 >Location:</strong> <strong>Walnut Creek Wetland Center</strong>\, 950 Pete
 rson St. Raleigh\, NC 27610</p><p></p><p>Calling everyone curious about bir
 ding\, but not sure where to begin!</p><p></p><p>‘Birding’ – or the observa
 tion of birds in their natural habitats as a hobby – has become one of the 
 most popular outdoor activities. If you are taking a new interest in birds 
 and looking for help getting started\, come develop your skills together wi
 th others at our Beginning Birding workshop.</p><p></p><p>This free public 
 program teaches the basics of bird identification\; how to use binoculars\,
  guides and apps\; types of bird safety and ways to bird safely\; and the i
 mportance of inclusion and allyship in birding and the outdoors. We’ll spen
 d time outside putting your learning to quick use.</p><p></p><p>Our route o
 utside will consist of flat\, paved concrete and asphalt trails. Gendered r
 estrooms will be available. Snacks\, coffee\, and tea will be provided.</p>
 <p></p><p>No binoculars? No problem! We have plenty of loaners to spare.</p
 ><p></p><p>Co-founded by <strong>Wake Audubon and Field Inclusive\, Inc.\, 
 in partnership with City of Raleigh Parks</strong>\, our mission is to prov
 ide safe\, equitable and accessible outdoor experiences for everyone.</p><p
 ></p><p><strong>Note: Participation may be capped due to space restrictions
 </strong>\, at which time <strong>notice of a wait list will be added to th
 e top of the registration form</strong>. Please continue to register to joi
 n the waitlist. Should we receive cancellations\, we’ll right away invite t
 hose on waitlist to confirm in the order registrations were received.</p><p
 ></p><p>Reach Wake Audubon board member\, Equity\, Diversity\, Inclusion an
 d Belonging co-chair and Beginning Birding program manager Rick LaRose at <
 a href="http://mailto:rlarose.was@gmail.com/">rlarose.was@gmail.com</a> wit
 h any questions.</p><p></p><p>We look forward to you beginning to bird with
  us on March 14!</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T022508Z
LOCATION:Annie Louise Wilkerson\, MD Nature Preserve Park\, 5229 Awls Haven
  Dr\, Raleigh\, NC 27614\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Beginner Bird for All
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
