BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/peter-francisco-commemoration-ceremony"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:Peter Francisco (1760–1831) was a Portuguese-born giant of the 
 American Revolution\, famed for his incredible strength and bravery in batt
 les like Camden and Guilford Courthouse. George Washington reportedly calle
 d him “a One-Man Army” and he was perhaps the most famous private soldier o
 f the Revolutionary War.\n\nCelebrated on March 15 in Virginia\, Peter Fran
 cisco Day honors the legendary bravery at the 1781 Battle of Guilford Court
 house\, where Peter fought valiantly against British forces and is remember
 ed on the American Cavalry Monument.\n\nJoin us on March 14 in Greensboro\,
  NC as we remember and honor Peter's bravery 250 years later.
DTEND:20260314T150000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260314T140000Z
GEO:36.13132;-79.84633
LOCATION:Guilford Courthouse National Military Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Peter Francisco Commemoration Ceremony
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51754034508673
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/peter-francisco-commemoration-ceremony
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260314T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260314T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082906802
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/women-at-the-edge-of-war-carolina-piedmonts-heroines-of-the-american-revolution"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:KMHM is excited to present Women at the Edge of War: Carolina P
 iedmont's Heroines of the American Revolution. This exhibit highlights the 
 daily courage and civic work of women in the Carolinas\, whose efforts were
  essential to Revolutionary resistance and survival on the southern frontie
 r.\n\nThe exhibit will run from Feb. 17\, 2026 to May 30\, 2026. The museum
  is open Tues-Sat\, 10-4. Admission is free. Check out kingsmountainmuseum.
 org or call 704-739-1019 for more information.
DTEND:20260314T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260314T140000Z
GEO:35.239004;-81.342181
