BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Wildlife Federation": "https://ncwf.org/event/invasive-plant-removal-huntersville/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_wildlife_federation
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260315T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260315T160000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212521
CREATED:20260212T142434Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260212T142435Z
UID:10001482-1773583200-1773590400@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:Invasive Plant Removal (Huntersville)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Charlotte Wildlife Stewards Chapter and community volunteers to remove invasive species at Unsheltered Tortoise and Turtle\, a local rescue and rehabilitation facility. Invasive plants are non-native introduced plants that do not support native wildlife. They are aggressive\, outcompete wildlife-friendly plants\, and take over natural areas. Removing invasive species is often the first step to enhancing and restoring habitat for wildlife. \nVolunteers will discover how to identify invasive plants\, including English ivy\, Nandina\, and Japanese honeysuckle\, and practice removing them by hand and with tools. Stick around after the event for pizza and a campfire! Please wear long sleeves and long pants. CLOSE-TOED SHOES ARE REQUIRED. AGES 13+ PLEASE. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/invasive-plant-removal-huntersville/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/CWSInvasiveRemovalUnsheltered.jpg
END:VEVENT
