X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:
DESCRIPTION:What began as a way to break up the winter doldrums and to invi
 gorate the community in preparation for the summer season\, the Kelly's St.
  Patrick's Day Parade in the Outer Banks of North Carolina\, has grown to i
 nclude over one hundred entrants and is watched by over eight thousand atte
 ndees making it the largest St. Patrick’s parade in North Carolina.\n\nCome
  out to cheer on the Jockey's Ridge State Park float as we march with Frien
 ds and community partners.  \n\nThis year's parade theme is America's 250th
  Anniversary and participants are encouraged to incorporate A250 in their f
 loat decorations. Dare County's A250 float will lead the parade\, accompani
 ed by Dare County Schools various marching bands playing patriotic music.\n
 \nThe Kelly’s Annual St. Patrick’s Parade will begin at 1 p.m. on Sunday\, 
 March 15 2026. The parade route runs from Bladen St. (MP 11.5) north to Dri
 ftwood St. on Virginia Dare Trail (Beach Road).
DTEND:20260315T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022457Z
DTSTART:20260315T170000Z
GEO:35.963597;-75.632255
LOCATION:Jockey's Ridge State Park\,  The parade route runs from Bladen St.
  (MP 11.5) north to Driftwood St. on Virginia Dare Trail (Beach Road).
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Kelly's 35th Annual St. Patrick's Parade/Jockey's Ridge State Park 
