DESCRIPTION:Link to join: https://www.mobilize.us/join/47683002/1:cfab6df4f
 04a3606b684c6430c1e14b7606e94a1e2ed1c1f44ccfdd8d2ed2f33/\n\nJoin Swing Left
  for a Ground Truth phone bank—designed to fix what’s broken in Democratic 
 organizing. We’re launching an innovative new program that will revolutioni
 ze how we connect with voters over the phone. \n\nOur goal: to help Democra
 ts rebuild trust\, win tough races\, and flip the House. We're bringing peo
 ple together to build the community of real people\, having real conversati
 ons with real people. During Ground Truth phone banks\, we will talk to as 
 many people as possible and focus on listening. \n\nAt this phone bank\, we
 ’ll:\n\n- Call ALL types of voters -- not just those who vote like us.\n\n-
  Have real conversations that LISTEN deeply to voters’ concerns.\n\n- Gathe
 r insights to share with campaigns\, so they can be responsive to voters’ n
 eeds and smarter with their messaging\, targeting\, and outreach.\n\nDon’t 
 worry if it’s your first time—training\, materials\, and support are all pr
 ovided. Just come prepared with your phone and laptop or computer!\n\nWe re
 commend using earbuds or using speakerphone to free up your hands as well! 
 \n\n––\n\nAbout the program:\n\nThis isn’t traditional phone banking—it’s a
  whole new way of talking to voters. Together\, we’ll gather authentic insi
 ghts from communities\, use cutting-edge tools to capture what we hear\, an
 d share it back with campaigns to strengthen their efforts.\n\nWhy we’re st
 arting early: We launched a year ahead of the midterms to build power befor
 e campaigns get off the ground.\n\nHow we’ll go big: Calling every voter\, 
 not just the ones we normally rely on\, so every conversation builds a more
  complete picture of the electorate.\n\nHow we’ll go deep: Practicing empat
 hetic listening and real conversations that uncover voters’ “Ground Truth\,
 ” not just checking boxes on a script.\n\nPaid for by Swing Left\, Swinglef
 t.org\, not authorized by any candidate or candidate’s committee.\n\nHow to
  prepare:\nThanks for signing up to join the Ground Truth phone banking pro
 gram! Together\, we can transform how we talk with voters\, rebuild trust\,
  and swing the most competitive races.\n\nThere will be a training at the b
 eginning of the phone bank\, so don't worry if this is your first time.  \n
 \nPlease be sure to have your laptop/ computer charged and ready to go!\n\n
 See you there!\n\nhttps://www.mobilize.us/swingleft/event/872281/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260122T231432Z
LOCATION:Virtual event
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Phone Bank with Ground Truth
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Eno River Association": "https://www.enoriver.org/events/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:eno_river
X-SOURCE:Eno River Association
URL:https://www.enoriver.org/events/
DTSTART:20260315T180000Z
DTEND:20260315T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022527Z
UID:5rkpp7ampcqd91tjlj650unbb6@google.com
CREATED:20260122T181343Z
DESCRIPTION:<b><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/guided-wildflower-hike
 -willie-dukes-bluff-tickets-1981356230823?aff=oddtdtcreator" target="_blank
 ">Registration is required -</a> </b>Tickets drop on February 1st at 8:00am
 !<br>Price: $4<br>*Ticket prices directly support the work of the Eno River
  Association. Thank you for your support!<br><p>This hike is somewhat diffi
 cult and will be off trail\, with some bushwhacking and one steep climb. Th
 is usually requires about three hours. If there have been recent rains\, pa
 rts of the trail may be muddy. The hike will lead you to a noteworthy natur
 al area called Willie Duke’s Bluff where you see outstanding displays of sp
 ring wildflowers\, including some that are rare and unusual in our area of 
 the Piedmont. The site boasts a showy display of spring ephemerals\, with e
 xtensive areas of Dutchman’s Breeches (Dicentra cucullaria)\, along with th
 e rare Eastern False Rue Anemone or Isopyrum (Enemion biternatum) and numer
 ous other wildflowers\, including Bloodroot (Sanguinaria canadensis)\, and 
 both Southern or Dimpled Troutlily (Erythronium umbilicatum)\, and its nort
 hern\, tetraploid counterpart (E. americanum). The shrub layer consists of 
 Spicebush (Lindera benzoin)\, Pawpaw (Asimina triloba)\, and Painted Buckey
 e (Aesculus sylvatica)\, which will be in various stages of flowering.</p><
 p>Wear sturdy shoes and long pants\, and bring gloves in case you feel incl
 ined to pull out any invasive Chinese privet seedlings that you might encou
 nter. You will also learn some history and geology along the way.</p><p>Ple
 ase feel free to bring water and snacks. Well-behaved dogs are welcome as l
 ong as they are under your control and on a 6-foot leash.</p><p>This event 
 is rain or shine. We will contact you if severe weather is expected that wo
 uld cause us to cancel the hike.</p><p>If your plans change and you are una
 ble to attend the hike\, please contact <a href="mailto:education@enoriver.
 org" target="_blank">education@enoriver.org</a> to cancel your registration
  so that we may offer your spot(s) to our waitlist.</p><p><br></p><p><stron
 g><strong>Directions: </strong></strong>Coming from the west\, take Duke St
 reet North from I-85 (Exit 176). Turn right on Murray Avenue (sign to the M
 useum of Life and Science)\, go until it reaches Roxboro Street\, turn left
  and look for the brown sign to Stagville. [Coming from the east\, you can 
 take Roxboro Street directly from I-85.] Turn right here on Old Oxford Road
 . Go about three miles until Old Oxford crosses the Eno. Immediately after 
 the bridge\, turn left on Snowhill Road. Penny’s Bend parking lot will be o
 n the left immediately after you turn.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260122T183039Z
LOCATION:Penny's Bend\, Old Oxford Rd\, Durham\, NC 27712\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ERA - Guided Wildflower Hike - Willie Duke's Bluff
