 m to 8:00pm</b><br>MacGregor Village STARBUCKS\, 101 S Edinburgh Drive\, Ca
 ry\, NC<br><br> We will be discussing <u style="font-weight: bold\;">Salmon
  Cannon and Levitating Frog</u> by<b> Carly Anne York</b><br><a href="https
 ://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-reviews/carly-anne-york/the-salmon-cannon-and
 -the-levitating-frog/" target="_blank">https://www.kirkusreviews.com/book-r
 eviews/carly-anne-york/the-salmon-cannon-and-the-levitating-frog/</a><br><b
 r>The author\, Carly Anne York\, shows how unappreciated\, overlooked\, and
  simply <b>curiosity-driven science</b> has led to breakthroughs big and sm
 all.<br><br>Our next meeting will be at 6:45 at Starbucks. We discuss the c
 urrent book\, and we encourage you to bring a readily-available book to sug
 gest for our next Book Club meeting. You are also encouraged to participate
  in our book exchange (bring books to give away or trade). Thanks<br><br><i
 >Please be prepared to make a small purchase to justify our free use of the
  conference room.</i>
