SUMMARY:Women's Social Hike
DESCRIPTION:Join TLC for a women's social hike!\nJoin other nature-loving women for a 1.5-hour hike in Johnston Mill Preserve at a moderate pace -- not speedy\, not slow\, just moderate.  On this hike\, you will experience a range of forest types while walking along New Hope Creek\, which meanders through the northeast portion of the preserve. \n Trail Guide Nancy will provide hot drinks at the end of the hike. This is a free event\, but preregistration is required. \n \nIf registration for this event is full\, please fill out the waitlist form here.  \n 
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/womens-social-hike-3
LOCATION:Johnston Mill Nature Preserve\, 2713 Mt. Sinai Rd.\, Chapel Hill\, North Carolina\, 27514\, United States
CATEGORIES:Hike,Social,Training,Workshop
