X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Cloud Security Alliance Triangle": "https://www.meetup.com/cloud-security-alliance-triangle-chapter/events/313298197/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_csa_triangle
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Cloud Security Alliance Triangle
UID:event_313298197@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260307T022537Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260319T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260319T200000
SUMMARY:CSA Triangle March Meetup - Sponsored by Tines
DESCRIPTION:Cloud Security Alliance Triangle Chapter\nAutomating the Cloud
  Controls Matrix: From Deterministic Audits to AI Agents\n\nModernizing GR
 C by evolving static risk workflows into intelligent AI agents that map se
 curity alerts directly to CSA standards\n\nSummary of Presentation:\n\nDes
 pite the rise of AI\, "manual work remains stubbornly high" for security t
 eams. This session demonstrates how to bridge the gap between CSA Cloud Au
 diting (CCAK) and practical automation by building a three-stage GRC pipel
 ine in Tines:\n1\\. The Foundation \\(Deterministic\\): We begin by ingest
 ing raw cloud alerts and creating a standardized "Risk Register using Tine
 s Records"\\\, ensuring every violation is captured without manual entry\\
 .\n2\\. The Intelligence \\(AI Agent\\): We upgrade the workflow with an A
 I Agent action\\. Because "Agents shouldn’t be a black box"\\\, we expli
 citly instruct it to map alerts to the Cloud Controls Matrix’s "197 cont
 rol objectives" and recommend remediation\\.\n3\\. The Interaction \\(AI C
 hatbot\\): We conclude by deploying an "AI interaction layer"\\. This allo
 ws auditors to query their compliance data using natural language \\(e\\.g
 \\.\\\, "Show me all GDPR risks"\\)\\\, effectively "unlocking AI’s full
  value" for the audit process
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/cloud-security-alliance-triangle-chap
 ter/events/313298197/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260210T200735Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260210T200735Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
