CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260204T141340Z
DESCRIPTION:Link to join: https://www.mobilize.us/join/48337654/1:50893fd56
 8165f3fef6e08031b2e24173b3b999662f1fc2f64d3d3d40e5ef6b3/\n\nHow to join:\nH
 EAL to Win School Board Campaign Training\nWhen: Mar 19\, 2026 07:00 PM Eas
 tern Time (US and Canada) \n\nRegister in advance for this meeting:\nhttps:
 //raceforward-org.zoom.us/meeting/register/Gzed0L12RAqL5TGHmLPvfQ \n\nAfter
  registering\, you will receive a confirmation email containing information
  about joining the meeting.\n\nIn recent years\, public schools and school 
 board meetings have become a central target for a growing authoritarian mov
 ement. These extremists are fomenting fear and division by contriving new c
 ontroversies around topics like book bans\, the rights of transgender stude
 nts\, and anti-"Critical Race Theory” attacks on curriculum. Thankfully\, p
 eople everywhere are standing up and fighting back. A counter-movement of c
 oncerned students\, parents\, educators\, and community members has arisen 
 organically in response to this growing authoritarian threat.\n\nRunning sc
 hool board candidates is an important way to fight for our children’s schoo
 ls\, and make sure every child can have a bright future. \n\nThat is why we
  need people like you everywhere to recruit\, support\, and elect leaders i
 n our communities who can serve as champions of public education as school 
 board members. \n\nWhether you're considering running yourself or supportin
 g someone else's campaign\, join this training to gain practical knowledge 
 about campaign essentials - from building an effective team to developing a
  winning field strategy to crafting messages that resonate with voters. \n\
 nThe training will also discuss how running a strong campaign can lay the g
 roundwork for "co-governance" - a transformative approach where elected off
 icials and community members collaborate to create lasting\, systemic chang
 e in our schools. \n\nThrough practical examples\, simple guidance\, and ac
 cess to additional resources\, you'll gain the confidence and clarity neede
 d to run effective school board campaigns to help build strong\, equitable 
 public schools that serve all students.\n\nhttps://www.mobilize.us/raceforw
 ard/event/894251/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260204T141340Z
LOCATION:Virtual event
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:School Board Campaign Training: Winning for our public schools\, ou
 r kids and our democracy
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
