SUMMARY:School's Out Camp: Garden Chefs
DESCRIPTION:Register Here\n\nGrades: 1st-3rd\nDate: Friday\, March 20\nTime: 9:00 AM – 3:00 PM  *Drop-off: 8:45 – 9:00 AM; Pick-up 3:00 – 3:15 PM\nLocation: North Carolina Botanical Garden\nFee: $75 ($68 Household & above Members)\nSchool Districts: Chapel Hill-Carrboro \n  \nSchool’s out for a teacher workday? Get your child outdoors and into nature at the Garden! Prepare to dig in and cook up some fun! In this tasty camp\, young chefs will explore how plants grow and discover the delicious ingredients that come straight from the garden. Campers will taste fresh veggies and learn simple\, kid-friendly recipes. The camp day will include garden explorations\, creative crafts\, and story time that celebrates the joy of growing and sharing food. From seed to snack\, it’s a day full of flavor and fun in the garden! \nLed by Garden environmental educators\, School’s Out Camps feature a blend of indoor and outdoor learning and loads of fun in a small group setting! \n  \nRegister Here
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/schools-out-camp-garden-chefs/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
CATEGORIES:Learn
GEO:35.901081;-79.031939
