BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Durham Central Park": "https://durhamcentralpark.org/upcoming-event/durham-farmers-market-8/2026-03-21/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:durham_central_park
X-SOURCE:Durham Central Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T120000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212504
CREATED:20251209T172901Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260225T191700Z
UID:13192-1774083600-1774094400@durhamcentralpark.org
SUMMARY:Durham Farmers' Market
DESCRIPTION:The Durham Farmers’ Market is a community of farmers\, growers and crafters. We are strongly committed to local products: every item you see at the market was produced by the people selling it\, and it all comes from no more than 70 miles away. \nThe Durham Farmers’ Market open Saturdays mornings for local produce\, flowers\, crafts and more! The Wednesday Market is open from 3-6pm Wednesdays\, Mid-April through Mid-October \nIf you’d like more information about this week’s vendor list\, SNAP benefits and map\, visit durhamfarmersmarket.com \n\nWe are happy to offer Double Bucks to our SNAP clients. This means is a SNAP client has $10\, they receive $20 in tokens to spend at the winter market.\n\nEstamos muy contentos de ofrecer Double Bucks a nuestros clientes de SNAP. Esto significa que si un cliente de SNAP gasta $ 10\, recibirá $ 20 en tokens para gastar en productos frescos.\n\n\nAdditionally\, we offer a cash match program for other qualifying folks. To receive this benefit\, simply bring cash to the info table. Then\, we’ll double the amount with tokens. For example\, $10 in cash equals $20 in tokens.\n\nTambién ofrecemos un programa de contrapartida en efectivo para nuestros beneficiarios de SNAP que no tienen beneficios durante el mes\, clientes de WIC y miembros de la comunidad que viven en viviendas públicas. Para recibir este beneficio\, simplemente traiga efectivo a la tabla de información y duplicaremos la cantidad con tokens. Por ejemplo\, $ 10 en efectivo equivalen a $ 20 en fichas.
URL:https://durhamcentralpark.org/upcoming-event/durham-farmers-market-8/2026-03-21/
LOCATION:Durham Central Park\, 501 Foster Street\, Durham\, NC\, 27701\, United States
CATEGORIES:Farmers' Market,Featured Events
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://durhamcentralpark.org/content/uploads/HuthPhoto-KAH_6070.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Durham Farmers' Market":MAILTO:info@durhamfarmersmarket.com
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Wildlife Federation": "https://ncwf.org/event/polk-street-pollinator-planting-charlotte/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_wildlife_federation
X-SOURCE:NC Wildlife Federation
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T110000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212521
CREATED:20260306T161140Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T161141Z
UID:10001509-1774083600-1774090800@ncwf.org
SUMMARY:Polk Street Pollinator Planting (Charlotte)
DESCRIPTION:Join NCWF Charlotte Wildlife Stewards Chapter and the city Tree Canopy Preservation Program to help create pollinator habitat along the Urban Arboretum Trail in Charlotte’s Greenville neighborhood. Pocket gardens are a great way to support pollinators and other wildlife by installing native plants. Volunteers will install hundreds of pollinator plugs and small containerized plants during this fun work day! \nPlease bring your favorite pair of gardening gloves. Tools will be provided but feel free to bring your own trowel! \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/polk-street-pollinator-planting-charlotte/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/PollinatorPlantingUAT.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Resilient Durham NC": "https://resilientdurhamnc.org/event/curating-change-the-art-of-activism-in-education/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:resilient_durham
X-SOURCE:Resilient Durham NC
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260321T160000
DTSTAMP:20260306T005621
CREATED:20260130T173732Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260130T173732Z
UID:4400-1774083600-1774108800@resilientdurhamnc.org
SUMMARY:Curating Change: The Art of Activism in Education
DESCRIPTION:we are invites you to join for their 10th Annual Let’s Talk Racism Conference! This year\, the theme is Curating Change: The Art of Activism in Education. The conference will be held in Durham at North Carolina Central University on Saturday\, March 21\, 2026\, and will provide an opportunity for educators\, parents\, students and community members to discuss creative ways of challenging racial inequities in our schools. \nThe purpose of this event is to give K-12 educators and pre-service teachers an opportunity to engage in sessions centered on building liberatory\, culturally affirming learning spaces that dismantle systemic racism in schools and beyond. CEU certificates will be provided for participating educators. While educators are the target audience\, we are welcomes all community members to participate. \nThe planning collaborative is thrilled to announce Keith Knight as their keynote speaker. Knight is an award-winning cartoonist\, musician\, and educator whose work has been lauded for its sharp wit\, political insight\, and ability to blend humor with hard truths. Best known for his comic strips The K Chronicles\, (th)ink\, and The Knight Life\, Knight has spent decades using comics as a lens to examine race\, class\, identity\, and the absurdities of everyday life. \nTo register\, visit www.LetsTalkRacism.com.
URL:https://resilientdurhamnc.org/event/curating-change-the-art-of-activism-in-education/
LOCATION:North Carolina Central University
ORGANIZER;CN="we are (Working to Extend Anti-Racist Education)":MAILTO:admin@weare-nc.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
