BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/remember-the-ladies-a-living-history-experience"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Remember the Ladies — A Living History Experience\n\nMuseum of 
 the Waxhaws • Waxhaw\, NC\nMarch 21 • 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM\n\nOn March 21st\,
  from 10 AM to 4 PM\, the Museum of the Waxhaws in Waxhaw\, NC will host “R
 emember the Ladies: A Living History Experience\,” an immersive event celeb
 rating the extraordinary women who helped shape America. Through first and 
 thid person interpretation and interactive storytelling\, guests will step 
 into the past and meet the women whose courage\, intellect\, and determinat
 ion influenced generations.\n\n Abigail Adams’ famous call to “remember the
  ladies” serves as the event’s guiding theme\, echoed throughout the day as
  performers illuminate the stories of women whose contributions are too oft
 en overlooked.\n\nIn addition to the living history presentations\, visitor
 s can enjoy a vibrant outdoor marketplace on the museum grounds. Women-owne
 d businesses\, artisans\, and makers will be onsite offering handcrafted go
 ods\, art\, specialty items\, and more. Food vendors will also be available
  on the outdoor field\, providing a variety of delicious options for guests
  to enjoy throughout the day.\n\nWith engaging activities\, meaningful conv
 ersations\, local vendors\, and lively performances\, this event offers som
 ething for all ages. Come spend the day with us as we honor the women of th
 e past\, support the women of today\, and celebrate the ongoing legacy of r
 esilience and inspiration.
DTEND:20260321T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260321T140000Z
GEO:34.920168;-80.734415
LOCATION:Museum of the Waxhaws
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Remember the Ladies: A Living History Experience 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51418658204878
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/remember-the-ladies-a-living-history-e
 xperience
END:VEVENT
