BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/jack-gates-wildflower-presentation-and-book-signing"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a presentation and book signing by author Jack Gate
 s\, who recently published Spring Wildflowers of Eastern Woodlands\, Photos
 \, Facts\, and Folklore. Jack's book is a culmination of 36 years of resear
 ch and discusses how wildflowers were used medicinally by Indigenous people
  and early settlers\, in folklore\, and as food. The presentation is free\,
  and books will be available for purchase.\n\nThe presentation is a great w
 ay to learn about the history of wildflowers and celebrate America's 250th 
 anniversary.  \n\nAbout America 250 NC\n\nAmerica 250 NC is North Carolina'
 s commemoration of the United States' 250th anniversary and is led by the N
 .C. Department of Natural and Cultural Resources. For more information abou
 t America 250 NC\, visit america250.nc.gov.\n\nPhoto credit: J. Shimel
DTEND:20260321T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260321T190000Z
