DESCRIPTION:Link to join: https://www.mobilize.us/join/47700460/1:f16743f49
 6a7c431f783e512fe225c85ac69706b6a3811c8038302c66c173b7c/\n\n#### Activist C
 are Program Workshop 1: Sustainable Activism at the End of the World (Janua
 ry 25th 2-4p)\n\nThis virtual workshop provides three frameworks for ideas 
 and tools to make your activism more sustainable. Former Indivisible Organi
 zer (TX/NM) Lauren Oertel will lead the group through discussions and strat
 egic problem-solving. You’ll leave the workshop with:\n\n- A worksheet iden
 tifying the framework and practice that most resonates with you\n- A plan t
 o implement that framework/practice to make activism more sustainable for y
 ou\n- Additional resources in support of this sustainability work\n\n#### A
 ctivist Care Program Workshop 2: Find Your Focus (February 22nd 2-4p)\n\nTh
 is virtual workshop provides the process for identifying which issues\, rol
 es\, and actions you will focus on to make your activism more sustainable. 
 Lauren will lead the group through discussions and planning activities. You
 ’ll leave the workshop with a plan\, resources\, and a worksheet identifyin
 g:\n\n- Your focus areas\n- The types of actions that best fit your energy\
 n- Your sources of joy/rest to tap into for the toughest days\n- Which role
 s\, issues\, and actions you’ll remove from your plate to prevent burnout\n
 \n#### Activist Care Program Workshop 3: Finding Joy in Darkness (March 22n
 d 2-4p)\n\nThis virtual workshop provides multiple frameworks for recognizi
 ng the origins of the darkness we’re navigating and how to connect with joy
  to make their activism in addressing that darkness more sustainable. Laure
 n will lead the group through discussions of panic v. safety/liberation zon
 es\, the window of tolerance\, etc. You’ll leave the workshop with a plan\,
  resources\, and a worksheet identifying:\n\n- Components of your safety/li
 beration zones\n- How you will spend more time in the Window of Tolerance t
 o take action with more ease\n\nhttps://www.mobilize.us/indivisiblecharlott
 enc/event/879630/
