DESCRIPTION:Explore three different visions and representative eras in the 
 history of our land: the early 18th century\, the American Revolution\, and
  the early 19th century with a presentation and update about current conser
 vation efforts\, programming\, and new research relating to the history of 
 this land. This program will go beyond the walls with a guided walk from th
 e library to Guilford's Witness Tree with time for reflection and learning 
 together in community. A partnership between Greensboro Public Library and 
 Guilford College\, this project is supported through a grant from America 2
 50 NC\, a program of the NC Department of Natural and Cultural Resources an
 d is the second of three related programs held at Greensboro sites in Sprin
 g 2026. To register\, email melanie.buckingham@greensboro-nc.gov
