DTSTAMP:20260307T022514Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260323T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T170000
SUMMARY:All Things AI 2026
DESCRIPTION:All Things Open RTP Meetup\nWe invite you to join us at All Th
 ings AI 2026. We've partnered with [The Artificially Intelligent Enterpris
 e (AIE) Network](https://theaie.net/) to bring you this event\, and we're 
 very excited! More than 1\,600 from all over the world attended last March
  (2025)\, and it was a tremendous success.\n\n**What is it?**\nAll Things 
 AI is an AI practitioners and users conference and community focused on te
 chnologies\, processes\, and people. The event is designed to provide worl
 d-class educational and networking opportunities to attendees.\n\n**[Websi
 te](https://2026.allthingsai.org/)**\n\n**Format:**\n**Monday\, March 23**
 \nTraining day with multiple paid workshops being hosted: **AI for DevOps*
 *\, **AIOS Workshop For Business Professionals**\, and **AI for Agents**. 
 A number of free workshops will be added soon\, to include Major League Ha
 cking's AI Roadshow.\n***\\*note\, separate registration is required for p
 aid and free workshops/sessions.***\n***\\*\\*A paid workshop registration
  on Monday DOES include Tuesday registration.***\n\n**Tuesday\, March 24**
 \nTraditional conference day with morning keynotes\, lunchtime AI Deep Tho
 ught (Lightning) Talks\, and 30-minute sessions across 7 tracks: **AI Buil
 ders**\, **AI Engineers**\, **AI Users**\, **AI Executives**\, **AI Govern
 ance**\, **Security & Compliance**\, **AI in the Enterprise (Transformatio
 n & Infrastructure)**\, and **Case Study / Demo**.\n***\\*note\, separate 
 registration is required for Tuesday***\n\n[See v 1.0 of the schedule here
 ](https://2026.allthingsai.org/schedule)\n\n**Speakers:**\nIncludes some o
 f the most well-known AI experts in the world from companies like AWS\, IB
 M\, Meta\, GitHub\, Block\, Fidelity Investments\, Truist\, AuthO/Okta\, N
 etflix\, Visa\, Apple\, Intuit\, Mistral AI\, and more.\n[See all speakers
  here](https://2026.allthingsai.org/speakers)\n\n**Food & Beverages:**\nLu
 nch (boxed lunch and drink) is included with paid registration for Monday 
 and Tuesday. Multiple restaurants are available and easily accessible in d
 owntown Durham around the conference venue.\n\n**Registration:**\nWe've wo
 rked hard to keep registration costs low and the event accessible. [Check 
 out the registration page here](https://2026.allthingsai.org/register).\n\
 n**Scholarships & Discounts:**\nWe understand personal situations and abil
 ity to pay varies\, so we've worked with partners to make a variety of sch
 olarships and discounts available. [See what's available here](https://202
 6.allthingsai.org/scholarships-discounts).\n\nQuestions? Contact us at **i
 nfo@allthingsopen.org**.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/all-things-open-rtp-meetup/events/313
 271067/
