DESCRIPTION:REGISTER HERE: <a href="https://righttobe.org/events/bystander-
 intervention-to-address-gender-based-street-harassment-3/">https://righttob
 e.org/events/bystander-intervention-to-address-gender-based-street-harassme
 nt-3/</a><br><br>As part of the <b>16 Days of Activism Against Gender-Based
  Violence</b> campaign\, <b>Right To Be</b> in partnership with the <b>NYC 
 Commission on Gender Equity</b> (CGE) and the <b>Mayor’s Office to End Dome
 stic and Gender-Based Violence</b> (ENDGBV)\, will host an online virtual b
 ystander intervention training to equip New Yorkers with tools to stand up 
 against harassment. The 16 Days campaign is a global initiative that runs f
 rom November 25 (International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against 
 Women) through December 10 (Human Rights Day)\, raising awareness to preven
 t and end gender-based violence. The training focuses on encouraging commun
 ity action\, offering practical strategies skills to safely intervene when 
 witnessing help someone who is experiencing hate-based harassment\, and joi
 n reinforcing the city’s commitment effort to <wbr />build fostering safer\
 , more equitable spaces for all.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260104T011559Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Right to Be's Bystander Intervention to Address Gender-Based Street
  Harassment
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
