BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/the-morbid-zoo-reevaluating-academia-for-the-internet-age"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:In 2019\, YouTube creator Mariana Colín started building her fi
 lm analysis YouTube channel\, The Morbid Zoo\, as an exercise in developing
  the video essay format as a legitimate mode of academic publishing. Since 
 then\, her videos have been viewed over 9 million times. YouTube is accessi
 ble and customizable\, offering a way to engage directly with a nonacademic
  audience. However\, it is also isolating\, biased toward particular kinds 
 of engagement\; it is also deeply politically fraught. In this talk\, Colín
  will share what she’s discovered about social media’s academic use — its s
 uccesses\, its failures and its possible futures.
DTEND:20260323T203000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022450Z
DTSTART:20260323T190000Z
GEO:35.78681;-78.665717
LOCATION:Caldwell Hall\, G107
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Morbid Zoo: Reevaluating Academia for the Internet Age
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52021466468793
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/the-morbid-zoo-reevaluating-academia-fo
 r-the-internet-age
END:VEVENT
