SUMMARY:Mosses of Duke Forest
DESCRIPTION:Spend an afternoon in Duke Forest with Blanka Aguero\, bryophyte data manager at the Duke University Herbarium\, learning about the common mosses of North Carolina woods. Learn about the biology of mosses and liverworts and gain basic moss identification skills as you explore a world beneath your feet.  Look for a separate program led by Blanka about the mosses of Duke Gardens on May 12. \nFee: $22; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code. \nLocation: Duke Forest; driving directions will be included in a program reminder email sent the week before the program. Parking is free and carpooling is encouraged.   \nAccessibility: This will be a small group program that takes place outdoors and traveling on unpaved trails with some uneven surfaces.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/botany-spotlight-mosses-of-duke-forest/
LOCATION:Duke Forest
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
