X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Durham Resistance": "https://durhamresistance.com/calendar"}
X-SOURCE-ID:durham_resistance_4
X-SOURCE:Durham Resistance
URL:https://durhamresistance.com/calendar
DTSTART:20260324T180000Z
DTEND:20260324T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022545Z
UID:6p5rjpjtovdvnnub4911a3rddc@google.com
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260104T011655Z
DESCRIPTION:REGISTER HERE: <a href="https://righttobe.org/events/how-to-res
 pond-2-0-practical-tools-for-being-powerful-in-the-face-of-harassment-6/">h
 ttps://righttobe.org/events/how-to-respond-2-0-practical-tools-for-being-po
 werful-in-the-face-of-harassment-6/</a><br><p>Building on Right To Be’s How
  to Respond to Harassment training and the methodology of Self Offense\, th
 is workshop dives deeply into the art of “reclaiming your space\,” Right To
  Be’s supportive skill for confidently responding to harassment. In today’s
  world\, where personal boundaries often feel increasingly challenged\, the
  power to respond confidently to harassment has never been more vital. We a
 ll deserve to feel safe and confident in our spaces\, but may hesitate to r
 espond in ways that honor both our instinctive reactions and our desire to 
 reclaim our power in these situations.</p><p>Pulling from Self Offense’s so
 matic and embodied expertise –  and 10 degrees of black belt between them –
  this training equips participants with:</p><ul><li>Simple tools to assess 
 situations objectively</li><li>Practical strategies to harness your natural
  responses</li><li>Concrete ways to set boundaries and reclaim your space</
 li><li>Real-world techniques for building lasting resilience</li></ul><p>Th
 rough guided practice and supportive discussion\, participants will gain pr
 actical experience in turning reactive moments into opportunities for empow
 ered action\, develop renewed confidence in their instincts\, and learn to 
 respond powerfully to harassment while staying true to themselves.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260104T011655Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Right to Be's How To Respond 2.0: Practical Tools for Being Powerfu
 l in the Face of Harassment
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
