DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260325T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260325T200000
SUMMARY:Wednesday night meditation circle
DESCRIPTION:Durham Plum Village Meditation Circle\nJoin us for a meditatio
 n circle in the Plum Village tradition of Buddhist teacher Thich Nhat Hanh
 . We will practice a short seated meditation (10 minutes)\, walking medita
 tion (10 minutes)\, dharma share on a topic of mindfulness by a fellow pra
 ctitioner\, group dharma sharing\, and singing. We actively welcome and af
 firm BIPOC and queer people and seek to hold an inclusive space for all.\n
 \n**Please note: Our location has changed to the Durham Friends Meetinghou
 se building in the Dogwood Room at 404 Alexander Ave\, Durham\, NC 27705**
 \n\nThe space has accessible parking\, entrances\, and gender neutral bath
 rooms. Chairs are available\, and we encourage you to bring a cushion with
  you if you have one.\n\nOur group is spirited\, compassionate\, and eager
  to learn mindfulness practices in community with one another. We have a s
 uggested $0-5 donation to cover the cost of the space\, with excess donati
 ons put toward group materials like spare cushions.\n\nPlease consider don
 ating to our group on Venmo: [@DurhamPlumVillageMeditation](https://accoun
 t.venmo.com/u/durhamplumvillagemeditation)\n\nIf you would like to be on o
 ur sangha email list\, please reach out to durhamplumvillagemeditation@gma
 il.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/durhamplumvillagemeditationcircle/eve
 nts/312671119/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260101T234738Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260101T234738Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
