X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/dr-mt-pope-house-presents-evelyns-book-club"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:This program honors Evelyn Pope by reading books. \n\nEvelyn\, 
 a college librarian born in 1908 and died in 1995\, loved a variety of book
 s from The Adventures of Tom Sawyer to Shakespeare and James Baldwin. The p
 rogram brings community members together monthly at the museum to discuss b
 ooks\, focusing on works by Black writers or featuring Black subjects\, inc
 luding fiction and non-fiction. Discussions will use questions to facilitat
 e conversation.\n\n"Mama Day" by Gloria Naylor\nWednesday\, Feb. 25\n "The 
 Black Angels: The Untold Story of the Nurses Who Helped Cure Tuberculosis" 
 by Maria Smilios\nWednesday\, April 22\n "A Visitation of Spirits" by Randa
 ll Kenan\nWednesday\, June 24\n "Becoming Lunsford Lane: The Lives of an Am
 erican Aeneas" by Craig Friend\nWednesday\, Aug. 26\n "Ring Shout" by P. De
 jeli Clark\nThursday\, Oct. 29Registration opens Jan. 23.  An optional book
  bundle will be available to purchase at registration. Books can be picked 
 up at the Dr. M.T. Pope House Museum.
DTEND:20260326T000000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260325T223000Z
GEO:35.77372;-78.638254
LOCATION:Dr. M.T. Pope House Museum
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Dr. M.T. Pope House Presents: Evelyn's Book Club
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51886320479167
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/dr-mt-pope-house-presents-evelyns-book
 -club
