DESCRIPTION:Come along for a Ranger-led morning birding walk at Mayo River 
 State Park. Fresh into the spring season\, enjoy the tranquil morning songs
  of our feathered friends while walking along the unmarked Mayo Meadows tra
 il. This trail is an easy hike through old tobacco fields and is about one 
 mile out-and-back length. \n\nMeeting location is at the Mayo River Bridge 
 Kayak Launch (3100-3110 US-220 BUS\, Stoneville\, NC 27048) parking lot. Pl
 ease bring outdoor shoes\, binoculars\, camera\, and a flash light. \n\nIf 
 you have further questions\, please call the park office at (336) 916-6080.
  \n\nPlease note: This event is subject to cancellation due to weather.
