X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/wilmington-ladies-tea-walk-251st-commemoration"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:The Burgwin-Wright House\, the oldest and largest historic site
  in Wilmington\, is partnering with the Wilmington Ladies Tea Walk chapter 
 to commemorate the 251st anniversary of the Wilmington Tea Party. Never hea
 rd of it? That's OK! The lesser known but still influential moment in histo
 ry was one of the last local acts of resistance against the Crown in the Ca
 pe Fear prior to the start of the American Revolution in the spring of 1775
 .\n\nAt the event\, guests will be able to explore the Burgwin-Wright House
  Gardens\, drink tea\, hear brief words from a few local historic experts a
 nd organizations\, and then join in a procession to the riverfront where te
 a will be burned in solidarity with this act of revolution at the eve of wa
 r. Registration is REQUIRED. Please call 910-762-0570 to register or with a
 ny questions!
DTEND:20260326T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260326T140000Z
GEO:34.235214;-77.946271
LOCATION:Burgwin-Wright House and Gardens
SEQUENCE:0
