BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UNC Chapel Hill": "https://calendar.unc.edu/event/cognitive-interviewing-in-survey-research-1333"}
X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:Cognitive interviewing in survey research is a tool that allows
  researchers to improve survey questions and questionnaires by better under
 standing how respondents understand and respond to the questions they are b
 eing asked. Data gathered through cognitive interviews help researchers ide
 ntify and remedy issues with their questionnaires. This short course provid
 es participants with\nfundamentals on where cognitive interviews fit in the
  survey process and on how to design\, conduct\, and analyze cognitive inte
 rviews. Participants will have the opportunity to practice specific cogniti
 ve interviewing techniques\, including think-alouds\, probing\, and observa
 tion. Participants will also learn about revising survey questions based on
  interpreting cognitive interview results and about the research on which c
 ognitive interview practices are based.\n\nCourse Goals:\nBy the end of the
  course\, participants will be able to:\n1. Understand what cognitive inter
 views are and their use in survey research\n2. Be able to prepare for and c
 onduct cognitive interviews\n3. Improve survey questionnaires and survey it
 ems based on cognitive interview data\n\nRegistration and fee (refundable f
 or students) are required for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260326T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022131Z
DTSTART:20260326T160000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Cognitive Interviewing in Survey Research
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50940251430327
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/cognitive-interviewing-in-survey-researc
 h-1333
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UNC Chapel Hill": "https://calendar.unc.edu/event/hybrid-lunchbox-talk-the-secret-life-of-ferns"}
X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:With Carl Rothfels\, Director\, Intermountain Herbarium\n\n \n\
 nThursday\, March 26\, 2026\n\n12:00 PM-1:00 PM ET\n\nHybrid - Join us in p
 erson or on Zoom!\n\nFree\; preregistration required. Register >\n\n \n\nWh
 at is a fern\, anyway? In this talk\, botanist Carl Rothfels will demystify
  (and maybe re-mystify) the fascinating world of ferns. He'll explore their
  unusual hidden biology\, provide tips for fern identification\, and introd
 uce some of North Carolina's outstanding fern diversity.\n\n \n\nABOUT THE 
 SPEAKER\n\nCarl Rothfels was born and raised in southern Ontario and was a 
 nature nerd from a young age. It wasn't until his PhD at Duke University\, 
 however\, that he caught the fern flu. Now a full-fledged pteridologist\, h
 e is the Director of the Intermountain Herbarium in Logan\, Utah\, where he
  gets to indulge his interest in botanical diversity and particularly his f
 ascination with the infamously confusing fragile ferns (Cystopteris).
DTEND:20260326T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022131Z
DTSTART:20260326T160000Z
GEO:35.899603;-79.03247
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Hybrid Lunchbox Talk: The Secret Life of Ferns
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52250927767383
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/hybrid-lunchbox-talk-the-secret-life-of-
 ferns
END:VEVENT
