DESCRIPTION:<p><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/eno-climate-champions-
 40-prairie-plantings-march-session-tickets-1982827853486?aff=oddtdtcreator"
  target="_blank">Registration required</a>.</p><p>Our annual <b>TEEN</b> En
 o Climate Champions program is back with a new twist! Local teens are invit
 ed to join the Eno River Association for a FREE four-session series focusin
 g on the role of <strong><strong>Piedmont prairie restoration</strong></str
 ong> in a changing climate. During these sessions\, students will learn abo
 ut the history and current status of Piedmont prairies\, the benefits of th
 ese ecosystems\, and how they can be reintroduced in the area.</p><p><b>In 
 this session\, participants will spend the first portion observing and lear
 ning about the Piedmont Prairie planting process with our Stewardship Manag
 er. We will then work together to install an informational kiosk that parti
 cipants will fill with their own Piedmont Prairie informational displays in
  the final session in April (date TBD).</b></p><p><strong><strong>Recommend
 ed ages 12-17 years old. Snacks provided!</strong></strong></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260213T135942Z
LOCATION:Confluence Natural Area\, 4214 Highland Farm Rd\, Hillsborough\, N
 C 27278\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ERA - Eno Climate Champions 4.0: Prairie Plantings
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
