X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Exhibitions,Films
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Women’s History Month by learning about the history o
 f the Cuala Press\, a small fine art press founded and led by Elizabeth and
  Lily Yeats\, sisters of poet William Butler Yeats\, in Ireland at the turn
  of the 20th century. The Yeats sisters hired Irish women to create hand-pr
 inted books\, publishing the works of emerging Irish authors and artists du
 ring a period of cultural revival and political change. View the documentar
 y film and explore original materials from the Cuala Press in Special Colle
 ctions.
DTEND:20260326T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022450Z
DTSTART:20260326T213000Z
GEO:35.787562;-78.669711
LOCATION:D.H. Hill Jr. Library\, Auditorium
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The Cuala Press and the Yeats Sisters: Film Screening and Exhibit
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51529958351327
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/the-cuala-press-and-the-yeats-sisters-f
 ilm-screening-and-pop-up-exhibit
