BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UNC Chapel Hill": "https://calendar.unc.edu/event/hanes-visiting-artist-lecture-series-fidenco-fifield-perez-3318"}
X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Lectures
DESCRIPTION:Department of Art and Art History\n\n \n\nFidencio Fifield-Pere
 z was born in Oaxaca\, Mexico\, but raised in the U.S. after his family mig
 rated. His current work examines borders\, edges\, and the people who must 
 traverse them. In his work\, Fifield-Perez’s interdisciplinary practice cen
 ters the materiality of paper ephemera\, everyday self- documents discarded
  after having fulfilled their purpose. For Fifield-Perez\, printmaking\, co
 llage\, and painting are ways to visualize and connect mental landscapes of
  past and present.\n\n \n\nFifield-Perez received his BFA from Memphis Coll
 ege of Art and an MA & MFA from The University of Iowa. He has exhibited at
  multiple institutions\, including The Cleveland Museum of Art\, the Herber
 t F. Johnson Museum of Art\, Marianna Kistler Beach Museum of Art\, the Mus
 eum of Contemporary Photography\, Chicago\, and International Print Center 
 New York. He has completed artist residencies at The Studios at MASS MoCA\,
  Ox-Bow\, ACRE\, Crosstown Arts\, and the Galveston Artist Residency\, amon
 g others. He has been awarded the Eliza Moore Fellowship at Oak Spring Gard
 en Foundation\, 2024 McKnight Printmaking Fellowship\, the inaugural Dr. Ha
 rold R. Adams Artist-in-Residence Fellowship at The University of Minnesota
  and is currently Assistant Professor of Painting at the University of Cali
 fornia-Davis.\n\n \n\nAn endowment established in 1983 through the generosi
 ty of Nancy and Robin Hanes supports the Art Department's Visiting Artist S
 eries. This important program brings both established and emerging artists 
 to campus to discuss their work in public lectures and to offer individual 
 critiques to our M.F.A. students.  The Hanes Visiting Artist series greatly
  enriches both our academic programs and our outreach to the wider communit
 y.  All lectures are free and open to the public.\n\n \n\nA weeknight or da
 ytime permit is now required after 5:00 pm on weekdays. No permit is requir
 ed from 5:00 pm Friday through 7:30 am Monday. A $1.00 one-night pass is av
 ailable in selected lots. More information can be found HERE.\n\n \n\nArtis
 t website: https://www.fidenciofperez.com/ \n\n \n\nContact: Martín Wannam\
 , mwanna@unc.edu
DTEND:20260326T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022131Z
DTSTART:20260326T213000Z
GEO:35.912392;-79.054366
LOCATION:Hanes Art Center\, 121 (Auditorium)
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Hanes Visiting Artist Lecture Series: Fidenco Fifield-Perez
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52242056841081
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/hanes-visiting-artist-lecture-series-fid
 enco-fifield-perez-3318
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/andrews-launch-accelerator-launch-sessions"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Training
DESCRIPTION:The Andrews Launch Accelerator's Launch Sessions are designed t
 o help ventures articulate\, validate and communicate their value to key pr
 ograms and stakeholders. The schedule for the Launch Sessions is below. All
  sessions will be held virtually.\n\nSession 1 (Feb. 26): Join us for an in
 troduction to the Andrews Launch Accelerator\, the Launch Sessions and the 
 first core principle: customer discovery.\n\nSession 2 ( March 5): This ses
 sion will explore the often-overlooked fundamentals of customer discovery. 
  It will focus heavily on understanding your customers' frustrations\, diss
 atisfactions and unfulfilled desires. The session will also delve into coll
 ecting evidence of these things through unbiased discovery work.\n\nSession
  3 (March 12): You'll learn about the methods entrepreneurs use to rapidly 
 validate demand for what they are working on without spending a lot of mone
 y and time.\n\nSession 4 (March 26): With just a few days left before the A
 ndrews Launch Accelerator applications are due on March 31\, this session w
 ill be an open-floor Q&A on anything related to the Andrews Launch Accelera
 tor\, including applications.
DTEND:20260326T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022450Z
DTSTART:20260326T220000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Andrews Launch Accelerator: Launch Sessions
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51939174095258
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/andrews-launch-accelerator-launch-sessi
 ons
END:VEVENT
