X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260327T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260327T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082920125
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/the-first-oval-office"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Homeschool & Education Days,Celebrations & Co
 mmemorations,Reenactments & Living History,Exhibits & Tours
DESCRIPTION:Experience George Washington’s Mobile Headquarters during the A
 merican Revolution!\n\nThe Museum of the American Revolution’s First Oval O
 ffice Project is coming to Tryon Palace and will be open for tours from Mar
 ch 26\, through 28. \n\nThe First Oval Office Project is an inspiring hands
 ewn\, reproduction of General George Washington’s mobile headquarters that 
 travelled with him throughout the American Revolution.  The reproduction en
 campment includes the sleeping and office marquee\, dining marquee\, baggag
 e tent\, camp bed\, furniture\, and more that were part of his mobile headq
 uarters while commanding the Continental Army\, as well as other tents for 
 common soldiers in the Continental Army.  A team of interpreters from the M
 useum of the American Revolution will be on site to guide you and answer qu
 estions about his military life while on campaign. Tryon Palace will be the
  only site in North Carolina to host the First Oval Office Project during 2
 026.  It is a “do not miss event” for all ages!\n\nThis is a specialty tour
  and requires a separate ticket.\n\nTo facilitate school groups\, general a
 dmission tickets are scheduled to begin Thursday and Friday at noon and at 
 10 A.M. on Saturday.\n\nThis event is funded by First Citizens Bank and the
  Mariam & Robert Hayes Charitable Fund.
DTEND:20260327T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260327T140000Z
GEO:35.104831;-77.043044
LOCATION:Tryon Palace Historic Sites and Gardens
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:The First Oval Office
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52250242102323
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/the-first-oval-office
END:VEVENT
