BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Triangle Land Conservancy": "https://triangleland.org/event/get-wild-pollinator-power"}
X-SOURCE-ID:triangle_land
X-SOURCE:Triangle Land Conservancy
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260329T133000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260329T153000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212504
CREATED:20260206T232635Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260206T232635Z
UID:10000035-1774791000-1774798200@triangleland.org
SUMMARY:Get Wild: Pollinator Power!
DESCRIPTION:Join TLC for a family friendly pollination exploration!\nPollinators run the world! As the first blooms of spring arrive\, so do their pollinators. Meet us at Williamson Nature Preserve's pollinator garden to learn about the special role of butterflies\, bees\, and more. Explore why pollinators matter with kid-focused nature games and learn to see the world through their eyes with a pollinator scavenger hunt! \n\nGet Wild! Hikes and activities are most appropriate for ages 5 years and up. Wear layers\, bring a water bottle\, and wear shoes that can get muddy. Please register all members of the family attending\, including children and adults. This is a free event\, but pre-registration is required:\n\n\nIf the event is full\, please email Meera Butalia at mbutalia@triangleland.org to be added to the waitlist.\n\nCurrent Mask Policy: TLC seeks to build a supportive\, mask-friendly environment in all collaborations with staff and the public. Please wear a mask if you are not vaccinated\, or if that makes you feel most comfortable. We also encourage those eligible to be vaccinated to get their Covid-19 vaccine and booster shot. If you are experiencing any Covid-related symptoms\, please stay home and attend a program another day. Our top priority is to create a safe environment for our community. Thank you for your understanding.\n\nInclement weather policy: In the event of inclement weather\, you will be contacted by email for a call on cancellation or postponement.
URL:https://triangleland.org/event/get-wild-pollinator-power
LOCATION:Williamson Farm and Nature Preserve\, 4429 Old Country Mial Rd\, Raleigh\, 27610\, United States
ORGANIZER;CN="Meera Butalia":MAILTO:mbutalia@triangleland.org
END:VEVENT
