DESCRIPTION:Link to join: https://www.mobilize.us/join/47683006/1:1d859d583
 8a314cd00eb29f52a62182ad856e0786f7b2c83e9dedb14ec5b21c5/\n\nJoin Swing Left
  for a Ground Truth phone bank—designed to fix what’s broken in Democratic 
 organizing. We’re launching an innovative new program that will revolutioni
 ze how we connect with voters over the phone. \n\nOur goal: to help Democra
 ts rebuild trust\, win tough races\, and flip the House. We're bringing peo
 ple together to build the community of real people\, having real conversati
 ons with real people. During Ground Truth phone banks\, we will talk to as 
 many people as possible and focus on listening. \n\nAt this phone bank\, we
 ’ll:\n\n- Call ALL types of voters -- not just those who vote like us.\n\n-
  Have real conversations that LISTEN deeply to voters’ concerns.\n\n- Gathe
 r insights to share with campaigns\, so they can be responsive to voters’ n
 eeds and smarter with their messaging\, targeting\, and outreach.\n\nDon’t 
 worry if it’s your first time—training\, materials\, and support are all pr
 ovided. Just come prepared with your phone and laptop or computer!\n\nWe re
 commend using earbuds or using speakerphone to free up your hands as well! 
 \n\n––\n\nAbout the program:\n\nThis isn’t traditional phone banking—it’s a
  whole new way of talking to voters. Together\, we’ll gather authentic insi
 ghts from communities\, use cutting-edge tools to capture what we hear\, an
 d share it back with campaigns to strengthen their efforts.\n\nWhy we’re st
 arting early: We launched a year ahead of the midterms to build power befor
 e campaigns get off the ground.\n\nHow we’ll go big: Calling every voter\, 
 not just the ones we normally rely on\, so every conversation builds a more
  complete picture of the electorate.\n\nHow we’ll go deep: Practicing empat
 hetic listening and real conversations that uncover voters’ “Ground Truth\,
 ” not just checking boxes on a script.\n\nPaid for by Swing Left\, Swinglef
 t.org\, not authorized by any candidate or candidate’s committee.\n\nHow to
  prepare:\nThanks for signing up to join the Ground Truth phone banking pro
 gram! Together\, we can transform how we talk with voters\, rebuild trust\,
  and swing the most competitive races.\n\nThere will be a training at the b
 eginning of the phone bank\, so don't worry if this is your first time.  \n
 \nPlease be sure to have your laptop/ computer charged and ready to go!\n\n
 See you there!\n\nhttps://www.mobilize.us/swingleft/event/872281/
LAST-MODIFIED:20260122T231218Z
LOCATION:Virtual event
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Phone Bank with Ground Truth
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UNC Chapel Hill": "https://calendar.unc.edu/event/mfa-2026-thesis-exhibitions-at-lump-gallery"}
X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Exhibits
DESCRIPTION:Department of Art and Art History\n\n \n\nLump Presents: UNC-Ch
 apel Hill MFA Thesis Exhibitions \n\nMarch 6th - March 29th:\n\nINFRA ULTRA
  by CJ Murphy / Under the Thumb by Michelle Lisa Polissaint\n\nOpening rece
 ption: March 6\, 6-9 pm\n\n \n\nApril 3rd - April 26th:\n\nNepantla by Wend
 y Yamilett Moran / Growing Elsewhere: Ghorbatī (غربتی) by Rojano Mohammadza
 deh / Blood\, Sap\, Dirt by Iris Moyan Wang\n\nOpening reception: April 3\,
  6-9 pm\n\nLump Gallery is located at 505 S. Blount St.\, Raleigh\, NC 2760
 1\n\nOpening Hours: Saturdays and Sundays\, 1-5 pm\, and by appointment.\n\
 n \n\nLump Gallery is pleased to present thesis exhibitions by UNC-Chapel H
 ill’s 2026 MFA graduating class. \n\n \n\nAt the conclusion of a rigorous\,
  research-based two-year program\, these artists consider the concept of pl
 ace and their personal relationships to it. Each artist employs a range of 
 media and responds to geographic\, constructed\, technological\, and bodily
  autonomy. These relationships between place and personal narrative raise b
 roader questions around positionality and society\; communication and ident
 ity\; and human impact. Revelation\, purpose\, and possibility guide each a
 rtist’s research-centered practices.\n\n \n\nCJ Murphy creates works that r
 ender the intersection of technology\, magic\, and globalization material b
 y reinvigorating found and discarded electrical waste. Michelle Lisa Poliss
 aint draws on her experience in a strict religious community and deep resea
 rch into the BITE method to discuss contemporary issues of indoctrination\,
  high-control groups\, and authoritarianism. Rojano Mohammadzadeh draws on 
 Islamic prayer\, talismanic imagery\, text\, and ritualized gestures to app
 roach the immigrant experience through what she terms transplantation: surv
 ival through negotiating acceptance within a host body. Wendy Yamilett Morá
 n’s practice explores the intersections of culture\, realism\, and spiritua
 lity through painting and ceramics\, using their work to examine how identi
 ty\, memory\, and belonging are shaped within in-between spaces. Iris Moyan
  Wang is an interdisciplinary artist working primarily with ink painting an
 d ceramics to create fluid and erotic hybridizations of bodies and botanica
 ls that reimagine Chinese cultural heritage.\n\n \n\nFor press inquiries or
  other questions\, please contact uncmfathesis@yahoo.com
DTEND:20260330T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022131Z
DTSTART:20260329T220000Z
GEO:35.773769;-78.636571
LOCATION:Lump Gallery/Projects
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:MFA 2026 Thesis Exhibitions at Lump Gallery
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52241621291973
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/mfa-2026-thesis-exhibitions-at-lump-gall
 ery
END:VEVENT
