CATEGORIES:Information Session
DESCRIPTION:Are you a science communicator\, interested in the science comm
 unication field or want to learn about science communication skills? Do you
  want to share your expertise in communicating science or share research wi
 th new audiences? Are you curious about how the arts can amplify your scien
 ce research? Are you an artist who works at the intersection of art and sci
 ence and wants to find science research partners for mutually rewarding art
 s-integrated research opportunities?\n\nScience communication is a rich fie
 ld made up of researchers and practitioners who understand that science res
 earch needs to be thoughtfully contextualized for increased impact on the p
 ublic good. Join Arts NC State\, the Office of Research and Innovation and 
 the College of Sciences for a meeting at the Gregg Museum of Art & Design t
 o share your expertise or learn about communicating science at NC State. Du
 ring the meeting\, you can propose ideas and topics for a series of Communi
 cating Science workshops that will be held during the 2026-2027 academic ye
 ar. We’d love for you to participate.
DTEND:20260330T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
