BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/spring-botanizing-at-pennys-bend/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260401T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260401T123000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20250106T194639Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230751Z
UID:10187-1775035800-1775046600@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Spring Botanizing at Penny's Bend
DESCRIPTION:Penny’s Bend\, an 84-acre preserve\, has a unique geology and therefore distinct soils that support rare plant species. Join Alec Motten\, professor emeritus\, and Paul Manos\, professor of biology\, Duke University\, for a relatively easy hike\, under two miles. The spring wildflower season is challenging to predict\, but we will see plenty! Plan to wear weather-appropriate\, comfortable clothes and good walking shoes. \nFee: $28; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code. \nLocation: Meet at Penny’s Bend. Driving directions will be included in a program reminder email sent the week before the program. Parking is free and carpooling is encouraged.   \nAccessibility: This will be a small group program that takes place outdoors and traveling on unpaved trails with some uneven surfaces and moderate inclines.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/spring-botanizing-at-pennys-bend/
LOCATION:Penny’s Bend Nature Preserve\, Old Oxford Rd\, Durham\, NC\, 27712\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/pennys-bend.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/nc-science-trails-scavenger-hunt"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:Birds and bicycles take center stage at Lake Norman State Park 
 in Troutman. Located in Iredell County 40 miles north of Charlotte\, Lake N
 orman State Park boasts the region's popular mountain biking trail system\,
  the Itusi Trail\, offering nearly 31 miles of single-track trail. The name
 sake lake is the largest manmade lake within the state\, and the park cover
 s about 17 miles of its northern shoreline. Park Lake\, set off from the la
 rger Lake Norman by a dam\, offers quiet fishing spots and paddling. Heron 
 rookeries on two islands shelter over 25 great blue heron nests. Join us at
  Lake Norman State Park for a fun Science Festival scavenger hunt during th
 e month of April to learn about science and nature at its finest!
DTEND:20260401T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260401T130000Z
GEO:35.67247;-80.932577
LOCATION:Lake Norman State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:NC Science Trails Scavenger Hunt
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52056435478020
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/nc-science-trails-scavenger-hunt
END:VEVENT
