CREATED:20260226T182848Z
DESCRIPTION:<p><u><u><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1983544839009?af
 f=oddtdtcreator" target="_blank">Registration is required</a></u></u> - Tic
 kets drop on March 1st at 8:00am!<br>Price: $4<br>*Ticket prices directly s
 upport the work of the Eno River Association. Thank you for your support!</
 p><p><br></p><p>Celebrate Earth Month with us for this special Wildflower W
 ednesday hike series at the Confluence! Join three guided hikes every other
  Wednesday in April to explore various trails at the Confluence\, based on 
 where the best spring blooms are at the time. The Confluence is a magical p
 lace for spring wildflowers!</p><p><br></p><p>Meet at the pavilion beside t
 he parking lot. This hike will take approximately two hours (sometimes less
 \, sometimes more). Please feel free to bring water and snacks. Wear comfor
 table\, weather-appropriate clothing and shoes. Well-behaved dogs are welco
 me as long as they are under your control and on a 6-foot leash. Restrooms 
 are available on-site.</p><p><br></p><p>The address is 4214 Highland Farm R
 d\, Hillsborough\, NC 27278.</p><p>From Hillsborough take Hwy 86 North away
  from town 1.6 miles from US70. Turn left on Coleman Loop 1.1 miles. Turn l
 eft on Highland Farm Rd 2.4 miles. The Confluence is on the left. There is 
 a large sign and a gravel driveway. From northern Orange County take Hwy 86
  south after passing Walnut Grove Church Rd take the first right on Kenion 
 Rd 1.7 miles. Turn right on Highland Farm Rd 0.6 miles. The Confluence is o
 n the left. There is a large sign and a gravel driveway.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T182848Z
LOCATION:4214 Highland Farm Rd\, Hillsborough\, NC 27278\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ERA - Wildflower Wednesday - Guided Hike - Confluence Natural Area
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
