BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/fulbright-networking-reception"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events,Student Life,Information Session,High-Impact Ex
 periences
DESCRIPTION:As part of NC State’s Fulbright Week celebration\, we invite yo
 u to attend the Fulbright Networking Reception!\n\n \n\nThis special event 
 will bring together previous and current Fulbright students\, faculty and s
 cholars to celebrate the research\, teaching and global experiences made po
 ssible through the Fulbright Program. It is an opportunity to connect with 
 members of our campus community who have participated in Fulbright exchange
 s and to learn more about how these transformative experiences advance rese
 arch\, public service and international collaboration.\n\n \n\nNC State wil
 l celebrate Fulbright Week in honor of the Fulbright Program’s 80th anniver
 sary\, recognizing eight decades of advancing research\, teaching and publi
 c service through global collaboration and life-changing opportunities for 
 students\, faculty and scholars. From March 30 through April 3\, NC State’s
  Office of Global Engagement\, Office for Faculty Excellence and the Univer
 sity Fellowships Office will host a series of informative and engaging even
 ts highlighting the many programs supported through Fulbright.\n\n \n\nFulb
 right is an academic and cultural exchange program that enables American st
 udents\, faculty and professionals to study\, teach and conduct research in
  more than 160 partner countries worldwide. Fulbright experiences foster la
 sting connections\, strengthen mutual understanding and support collaborati
 ve solutions to global challenges.\n\n \n\nWe hope you will join us to cele
 brate NC State’s Fulbright community and explore how you can be part of thi
 s global network! This event is sponsored by the Fulbright Association and 
 will include remarks on Fulbright’s mission for global initiatives by Vice 
 Provost for Global Engagement Dr. Amy Conger and Vice Provost of Faculty Ex
 cellence Kim Grainger\, followed by a slideshow of Fulbright experiences\, 
 networking session and hors d’oeuvres.
DTEND:20260402T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260402T190000Z
GEO:35.784114;-78.671321
LOCATION:Talley Student Union\, 3210
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Fulbright Networking Reception 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52276835955991
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/fulbright-networking-reception
END:VEVENT
