DESCRIPTION:<p>Early Bird at <strong>Horseshoe Farm Nature Preserve</strong
 > (registration required off Meetup)</p><p><strong>Saturday\, APRIL 4\, 202
 6\, 8 am - 9:30 am</strong></p><p>Register Off-site only: Requires a login 
 and password:</p><p>Login first at <a href="https://ncraleighweb.myvscloud.
 com/webtrac/web/splash.html" target="_blank">https://ncraleighweb.myvscloud
 .com/webtrac/web/splash.html</a></p><p>Then register for this free event at
 :<br></p><p><a href="https://ncraleighweb.myvscloud.com/webtrac/web/iteminf
 o.html?Module=AR&amp\;FMID=441387752">https://ncraleighweb.myvscloud.com/we
 btrac/web/iteminfo.html?Module=AR&amp\;FMID=441387752</a></p><p>Or Click on
  Search -- Activity Search and type in "EARLY BIRD"</p><p>Grab your binocul
 ars and meet us at beautiful <strong>Horseshoe Farm Nature Preserve</strong
 > for a bird-watching hike led by Wake Audubon guest naturalist\, <b>Royce 
 Marcus</b> <i>(substituting for Erla Beegle) </i><strong>.</strong> Spend y
 our morning watching and learning about birds that prefer meadows and fores
 t edges on this approximately 1.5 mile hike. For beginning and advanced bir
 ders. Bring your binoculars\, or borrow a pair of ours. Pre-registration is
  required. Limited to City of Raleigh residents.</p><p>Meet in the parking 
 lot at Horseshoe Farm Nature Preserve <b>2900 Horseshoe Farm Rd\,</b> Wake 
 Forest\, NC\, 27587 . Note: Allow time for road construction at 401 and Lig
 on Mill Road.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251214T134522Z
LOCATION:Horseshoe Farm Nature Preserve\, 2900 Horse Shoe Farm Rd\, Wake Fo
 rest\, NC 27587\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Horseshoe Farm - City birdwalk
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
