BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/botany-by-plant-family-the-key-to-see-2/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260405T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260405T163000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20251208T230718Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230718Z
UID:14688-1775394000-1775406600@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Botany by Plant Family: The Key to See
DESCRIPTION:Learning to notice plant family patterns can greatly aid in demystifying the “green wall” of plant species around us. Nearly 350\,000 species of flowering plants are known to global science\, and these species have been grouped into more than 400 flowering plant families. By learning the top 30 plant families growing around you\, you will begin to recognize plants everywhere you go. After an indoor presentation on the major plant families common to the Southeastern U.S.\, ethnobotanist marc williams will reinforce your plant identification skills on a walk in the Gardens to observe family patterns in leaf\, flower and fruit types. Discuss edibility\, medicinality\, craft\, wildlife support and landscape beauty as you gain a more holistic understanding of the major plants comprising Southern U.S. flora and their potential ecological and ethnobotanical applications. \nFee: $32; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code. \nParking: Fees apply. \nLocation: Onsite at Duke Gardens. Meeting location will be included in a program reminder email sent before the program. \nAccessibility: This will be a small group program that takes place partially seated indoors and partially outdoors traveling on a combination of paved and unpaved paths with some uneven surfaces and moderate inclines.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/botany-by-plant-family-the-key-to-see-2/
LOCATION:Onsite at Duke Gardens – directions to follow
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/lannon-desert-poppy-scree-garden-terraces-4-18-24-5-scaled.jpg
END:VEVENT
