X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Raleigh AI, ML & Computer Vision": "https://www.meetup.com/raleigh-ai-machine-learning-and-computer-vision-meetup/events/313298936/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_raleigh_ai_ml_cv
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Raleigh AI, ML & Computer Vision
UID:event_313298936@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260307T022534Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260408T140000
SUMMARY:April 8 - Getting Started with FiftyOne
DESCRIPTION:Raleigh AI\, Machine Learning and Computer Vision Meetup\nThis
  workshop provides a technical foundation for managing large scale compute
 r vision datasets. You will learn to curate\, visualize\, and evaluate mod
 els using the [open source FiftyOne app](https://docs.voxel51.com/).\n\n**
 Date\, Time and Location**\n\nApr 8\, 2026\n10 AM PST - 11 AM Pacific\nOnl
 ine. **[Register for the Zoom!](https://voxel51.com/events/getting-started
 -with-fiftyone-april-8-2026)**\n\nThe session covers data ingestion\, embe
 dding visualization\, and model failure analysis. You will build workflows
  to identify dataset bias\, find annotation errors\, and select informativ
 e samples for training. Attendees leave with a framework for data centric 
 AI for research and production pipelines\, prioritizing data quality over 
 pure model iteration.\n\nWhat you'll learn\n\n* **Structure unstructured d
 ata.** Map data and metadata into a queryable schema for images\, videos\,
  and point clouds.\n* **Query datasets with the FiftyOne SDK**. Create com
 plex views based on model predictions\, labels\, and custom tags. Use the 
 FiftyOne to filter data based on logical conditions and confidence scores.
 \n* **Visualize high dimensional embeddings**. Project features into lower
  dimensions to find clusters of similar samples. Identify data gaps and ou
 tliers using FiftyOne Brain.\n* **Automate data curation.** Implement algo
 rithmic measures to select diverse subsets for training. Reduce labeling c
 osts by prioritizing high entropy samples.\n* **Debug model performance.**
  Run evaluation routines to generate confusion matrices and precision reca
 ll curves. Visualize false positives and false negatives directly in the A
 pp to understand model failures.\n* **Customize FiftyOne**. Build custom d
 ashboards and interactive panels. Create specialized views for domain spec
 ific tasks.\n\n**Prerequisites:**\n\n* Working knowledge of Python and mac
 hine learning and/or computer vision fundamentals.\n* All attendees will g
 et access to the tutorials and code examples used in the workshop.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/raleigh-ai-machine-learning-and-compu
 ter-vision-meetup/events/313298936/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260210T203209Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260210T203209Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/big-tree-paddle"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes)
DESCRIPTION:Few people know about the "Big Tree" at Merchants Millpond\, an
 d even fewer have actually been to it. \n\nThe "Big Tree"\, as many call it
 \, is actually the second largest tree in the state of North Carolina\, and
  we periodically lead paddles to it. Be warned: this is an all day adventur
 e and not for the faint of heart. This paddle lasts from about 9AM-4PM but 
 it is well worth it! Paddlers should bring appropriate clothing\, plenty of
  water\, a packed lunch\, and sunscreen. A good hat is also recommended. De
 pending on water level of the millpond\, there is always a chance paddlers 
 will have to drag boats over beaver dams. There is a limited number of spot
 s for this evet and registration prior to the event date is required. \n\nC
 ome out and learn about some of the things that make Merchants Millpond suc
 h an interesting place to be!\n\nWe will leave at 9:00 AM sharp. Please mee
 t at the visitor center around 8:30 AM for orientation. \n\nTo register\, p
 lease call the visitor center at 252-357-1191
DTEND:20260408T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260408T130000Z
GEO:36.437278;-76.701271
LOCATION:Merchants Millpond State Park
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Big Tree Paddle
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52259345693471
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/big-tree-paddle
END:VEVENT
