X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Durham Resistance": "https://durhamresistance.com/calendar"}
X-SOURCE-ID:durham_resistance_4
X-SOURCE:Durham Resistance
URL:https://durhamresistance.com/calendar
DTSTART:20260409T140000Z
DTEND:20260409T143000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022545Z
UID:3fnor8f6fot1rib828o0036j8p@google.com
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260104T011835Z
DESCRIPTION:REGISTER HERE: <a href="https://righttobe.org/events/bystander-
 intervention-to-stop-online-harassment-how-to-be-an-ally-when-you-witness-a
 buse-online-7/">https://righttobe.org/events/bystander-intervention-to-stop
 -online-harassment-how-to-be-an-ally-when-you-witness-abuse-online-7/</a> <
 br><br><section><br><br><br><p>PEN America and Right to Be have partnered t
 o provide training on how to intervene safely when you see a journalist att
 acked online. This training is also brought to you in partnership with the 
 NYC Commission on Gender Equity\, the Mayor’s Office of Equity and Racial J
 ustice\, and the NYC Commission on Gender Equity.</p><br><p>In this free\, 
 one-hour\, interactive training\, we’ll give you the tools you need to inte
 rvene safely and effectively in online abuse using Right To Be’s 5Ds of bys
 tander intervention. First\, we’ll talk through what online harassment is a
 nd how to identify abusive tactics. We’ll discuss the severe impact online 
 abuse can have – on well being\, livelihoods\, and free expression – and ho
 w it’s drowning out voices that urgently need to be heard in public discour
 se. Then\, we’ll share concrete strategies for how to distract\, delegate\,
  document\, delay\, or directly intervene in a way that is safe\, effective
 \, and centered on the needs of the person being targeted.</p><p>We’ll have
  time to practice so you can leave feeling more confident intervening the n
 ext time you see someone being abused online. We hope you’ll join us to lea
 rn how we can all band together to do your part to protect press freedom an
 d defend the media from attacks on their independence\, including online ab
 use and threats.</p></section><section><br><br></section>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260104T011835Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Right to Be's Bystander Intervention to Stop Online Harassment: How
  to Be an Ally When You Witness Abuse Online
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
