X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs,Reenactments & L
 iving History
DESCRIPTION:Join the Alliance for Historic Hillsborough as we invite you to
  immerse yourself in the captivating history of the American Revolution thr
 ough a day of FREE\, family-friendly events! Featuring reenactors\, dancers
 \, captivating historic tours\, interactive activities\, and collaborative 
 events throughout the town\, this is a day of enriching experiences for all
  to enjoy.\n\n>>> REGISTRATION is recommended\, not required <<<\n\nEVENT H
 IGHLIGHTS\n\nHillsborough Visitor Center - 150 E KING\n\n-23rd Regiment Roy
 al Welch Fusiliers of Foot\n\n-Live colonial fiddle music by Shane Watson\n
 \n-Guilford Courthouse living history interpreters\n\n-Colonial surgeon Mik
 e Williams medical demonstrations\n\n-Author Suzanne Adair book signing and
  meet and greet\n\n-Colonialfoodways\, crafts demos\, Hills Academy talks\,
 and -SugarSpun lemonade refreshments\n\n-Revolutionary-Era and Outlander Hi
 story Walking Tours Available for Purchase\n\n \n\nThe Burwell School Histo
 ric Site - 319 N CHURTON\n\n- Sun Assembly County Dancers perform\n\n-High 
 Point Museum pop up exhibit\n\n-Quill and ink writing station\n\n-Self guid
 ed historic site tours\n\n-Historic schoolhouse open house\n\n-A250 childre
 n’s comic display\n\n \n\nOrange County Historical Museum - 201 N CHURTON\n
 \n-Special display on Colonial currency\n\n-New exhibit: United We Stand\, 
 Divided We Fall\n\n \n\nOccaneechi Replica Village - 140 E MARGARET LANE\n\
 n-Foodways reenactment\n\n-Colonial era trading demonstrations\n\n-Historic
  structure living history tours\n\n-History table featuring Occaneechi Band
  of the Saponi Nation Scholar Lawrence Dunmore III
DTEND:20260412T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260412T020000Z
GEO:56.000456;-4.71344
LOCATION:Hillsborough Visitor Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Revolutionary War Living History Day
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52267412495967
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/revolutionary-war-living-history-day
