BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/prelude-to-revolution-halifax-resolves-days-8330"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the 250th anniversary of the Halifax Resolves\, the f
 irst official action by an entire colony recommending independence from Gre
 at Britain.  On Friday and Saturday\, enjoy two days of living-history acti
 vities\, historic weapons demonstrations\, military drills\, and interact w
 ith characters from Halifax’s past. Guest speakers will also give presentat
 ions on various topics. On Sunday\, the living-history activities will cont
 inue.  In the afternoon\, the NC Society Sons of the American Revolution wi
 ll host their annual wreath-laying ceremony\, and the Historical Halifax Re
 storation Association will host the annual Halifax Day ceremony\, followed 
 by a reception.  Free.
DTEND:20260412T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260412T140000Z
GEO:36.329317;-77.588638
LOCATION:Historic Halifax
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Prelude to Revolution: Halifax Resolves Days
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51586036541942
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/prelude-to-revolution-halifax-resolves
 -days-8330
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260412T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022458Z
DTSTART:20260412T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082933451
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/bike-maintenance-class-group-ride"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Every second Sunday\, get your biking fix with the Greenway Gea
 r Collective's Bike Maintenance Class and Group Ride. Their 10 a.m. monthly
  basic maintenance class is a great way to learn the essentials of bike car
 e and tune-ups. Each class is shaped by the needs of those who show up with
  no two being the same.\n\nThen at noon\, you can join a themed group ride 
 starting and ending at The Bike Library container on the shores of Lake Ral
 eigh. Bring your own bike or rent one of theirs. Feel free to show up for t
 he class\, the group ride or both.\n\nWhile both of these events are drop-i
 n accessible and encouraged\, signing up in advance for the class or pre-fi
 lling out the waiver for the ride is always greatly appreciated.
DTEND:20260412T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260412T140000Z
GEO:35.767879;-78.677586
LOCATION:Lake Raleigh\, The Bike Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Bike Maintenance Class and Group Ride
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51435730101165
