DESCRIPTION:<p><u><u><a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/1984072603567?af
 f=oddtdtcreator" target="_blank">Registration is required</a></u></u> - Tic
 kets drop on March 1st at 8:00am!<br>Price: $4<br>*Ticket prices directly s
 upport the work of the Eno River Association. Thank you for your support!</
 p><p><br></p><p>This guided hike will explore various trails at the Conflue
 nce\, based on where the best spring blooms are at the time. The Confluence
  is a magical place for spring wildflowers!</p><p><br></p><p>Meet at the pa
 vilion beside the parking lot. This hike will take approximately two hours 
 (sometimes less\, sometimes more). Please feel free to bring water and snac
 ks. Wear comfortable\, weather-appropriate clothing and shoes. Well-behaved
  dogs are welcome as long as they are under your control and on a 6-foot le
 ash. Restrooms are available on-site.</p><p><br></p><p>The address is 4214 
 Highland Farm Rd\, Hillsborough\, NC 27278.</p><p>From Hillsborough take Hw
 y 86 North away from town 1.6 miles from US70. Turn left on Coleman Loop 1.
 1 miles. Turn left on Highland Farm Rd 2.4 miles. The Confluence is on the 
 left. There is a large sign and a gravel driveway. From northern Orange Cou
 nty take Hwy 86 south after passing Walnut Grove Church Rd take the first r
 ight on Kenion Rd 1.7 miles. Turn right on Highland Farm Rd 0.6 miles. The 
 Confluence is on the left. There is a large sign and a gravel driveway.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T182716Z
LOCATION:4214 Highland Farm Rd\, Hillsborough\, NC 27278\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:ERA - Guided Wildflower Hike - Confluence Natural Area
