CATEGORIES:High-Impact Experiences
DESCRIPTION:Join NC State Dining for an immersive Earth Month experience as
  we explore the journey of food from farm to table. We'll meet outside of F
 ountain Dining Hall at 9:30 a.m. From there\, we'll take a bus to the NC St
 ate Compost Facility and Research Cooperative to learn how food waste from 
 the dining halls is turned into a nutrient-rich soil amendment. Our second 
 stop will be at the Agroecology Education Farm to see how that compost is u
 tilized and how food is grown on campus. Lastly\, we'll close the loop and 
 enjoy lunch at Fountain Dining Hall\, featuring some of the produce from th
 e Agroecology Education Farm.
DTEND:20260413T163000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260413T133000Z
GEO:35.785467;-78.677626
LOCATION:Fountain Dining Hall
