 s and tools for optimizing the reach of their work. Attendees will gain a s
 eries of strategic skills to help ensure their published research reaches a
  wide audience and its research impact can be tracked.\n\nTopics covered wi
 ll include:\n\nResearch impact measurement optionsOptimizing abstract writi
 ng for database discoverabilityWriting a plain language summary of a studyB
 enefits of ORCID and how to set up an ORCIDUnderstanding open access publis
 hing and author rightsThis workshop is offered by the UNC Health Sciences L
 ibrary and led by Emma Barrett-Catton
