BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/3rd-annual-legal-history-lecture"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Please join the Department of History at the third annual Legal
  History Lecture. This public event is part of the department’s legal histo
 ry programming and honors the memory of Jonathan Ocko\, who served as head 
 of the history department and was a department faculty member. Ocko was als
 o a Chinese legal historian.\n\nThis event will feature Marcus Gadson\, a U
 NC-Chapel Hill School of Law associate professor and a Harvard Law graduate
  who is a leading authority on state constitutions. He has published work i
 n top-tier journals\, including the New York University\, Michigan and Geor
 getown law reviews. Gadson is the author of Sedition: How America’s Constit
 utional Order Emerged From Violent Crisis. Previously\, he practiced at Ste
 ptoe & Johnson and clerked for Sixth Circuit U.S. Court of Appeals Judge Be
 rnice Donald.
DTEND:20260415T214500Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260415T203000Z
LOCATION:Park Shops\, 210
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:3rd Annual Legal History Lecture
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52143213315653
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/3rd-annual-legal-history-lecture
END:VEVENT
