BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/geospatial-forum-global-data-for-local-action"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:The Geospatial Forum will host a lecture by Ted Wong\, a data s
 cientist and research associate on the Urban Analytics team at the World Re
 sources Institute's Ross Center for Sustainable Cities.\n\nThe World Resour
 ces Institute (WRI) is a large environmental nongovernmental organization t
 hat provides geospatial data and analyses to local governments to support s
 ustainable urban planning. This talk will examine how WRI builds and deploy
 s data products supporting city-level planning and decision-making for extr
 eme heat\, urban biodiversity and decarbonization. We will discuss theories
  of change\, user research\, project-level business models\, strategies for
  mainstreaming\, representation of uncertainty and all the technical consid
 erations behind our data products.
DTEND:20260416T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260416T190000Z
GEO:35.781776;-78.67626
LOCATION:Jordan Hall\, 5111
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Geospatial Forum: Global Data for Local Action
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51835008012128
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/geospatial-forum-global-data-for-local-
 action
