LAST-MODIFIED:20251202T180134Z
UID:10000825-1776420000-1776423600@ncbg.unc.edu
SUMMARY:Nature Tales: Wiggly Worms
DESCRIPTION:Register Here\n\nAges: 3-7 with accompanying adult\nDate: Friday\, April 17\nTime: 10:00 – 11:00 a.m.\nLocation: North Carolina Botanical Garden\nFee: Free; pre-registration required. \n  \nEver wonder what worms do all day underground? Join us for stories about these squiggly soil superheroes and discover the secret life of the creatures beneath our feet. \nThe program will happen rain or shine\, with indoor activities if the weather is unfavorable. This family-friendly program has been designed especially for children ages 3-7. \n  \nRegister Here
URL:https://ncbg.unc.edu/event/nature-tales-wiggly-worms/
LOCATION:North Carolina Botanical Garden\, 100 Old Mason Farm Road\, Chapel Hill\, NC\, 27517\, United States
