BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/kiana-bonollo-how-i-built-a-fashion-career-using-social-media"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Lectures and Talks
DESCRIPTION:Kiana Bonollo '21\, Content Creator and Patternmaker\n\nTalk: H
 ow I Built a Fashion Career Using Social Media\nFrom YouTube to Digital Pro
 ducts\, Brand Partnerships & Entrepreneurship\n\nWhat began as posting sewi
 ng projects on YouTube evolved into a multi-platform business built on digi
 tal sewing patterns\, online education\, and brand partnerships. In this ta
 lk\, Kiana walks through how she identified a gap in the market\, listened 
 to her audience\, and turned technical design skills into scalable digital 
 products.\n\nShe will explore how social media has transformed entrepreneur
 ship in the fashion industry: lowering marketing barriers\, creating direct
  access to consumers\, and opening new career paths beyond traditional corp
 orate roles. Students will learn how to think strategically about social pl
 atforms\, whether as influencers\, entrepreneurs\, or designers building th
 eir own brands.\n\nThe event is free but has limited capacity. Stay tuned f
 or registration details!
DTEND:20260421T233000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260421T220000Z
GEO:35.770005;-78.67824
LOCATION:Wilson College of Textiles\, W. Duke Kimbrell Atrium
SEQUENCE:0
