URL:https://durhamresistance.com/calendar
DTSTART:20260422T170000Z
DTEND:20260422T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022545Z
UID:7a0lh17pcgev5je0babqc54l2e@google.com
CLASS:PUBLIC
CREATED:20260104T011922Z
DESCRIPTION:REGISTER HERE: <a href="https://righttobe.org/events/bystander-
 intervention-to-stop-islamophobic-and-xenophobic-harassment-13/">https://ri
 ghttobe.org/events/bystander-intervention-to-stop-islamophobic-and-xenophob
 ic-harassment-13/</a><br><br>This 75-minute interactive training\, brought 
 to you by Right To Be\, in partnership with the NYC Commission on Gender Eq
 uity\, the Mayor’s Office of Equity and Racial Justice\, and the NYC Commis
 sion on Gender Equity\, will teach you Right To Be’s 5Ds of bystander inter
 vention methodology. We’ll start by talking about the types of disrespect t
 hat Muslims and those who are perceived to be Muslim are facing right now —
  from microaggressions to violence — using a tool we call the “spectrum of 
 disrespect.” You’ll learn what to look for and the positive impact that bys
 tander intervention has on individuals and communities. We’ll talk through 
 five strategies for intervention: distract\, delegate\, document\, delay\, 
 and direct\, and how to prioritize your own safety while intervening. We’ll
  have time at the end for practice\, and you’ll leave feeling more confiden
 t intervening the next time you see Islamophobic and xenophobic harassment 
 online or in person.
LAST-MODIFIED:20260104T011922Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Right to Be's Bystander Intervention to Stop Islamophobic and Xenop
 hobic Harassment
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
