BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/nc_state_earth_day_clean_up"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Come volunteer and celebrate Earth Month by spending a few hour
 s beautifying Lake Raleigh\, a 75-acre lake amid a 96-acre protected forest
 \, April 24. Earth Day is April 22.\n\nVolunteer tasks will include collect
 ing litter along greenway trails\, natural trails and Lake Raleigh.\n\nTrai
 ning and volunteering: All volunteers must attend a safety training session
  at 10 a.m. You can decide how long to volunteer. The clean-up effort will 
 conclude by noon.\n\nWhere to join us and park: You can join the volunteer 
 effort at either of the following locations:\n\nThe Lake Raleigh fishing pi
 er: If you plan to walk or ride a bike or the bus from campus\, consider me
 eting us at the fishing pier. Paid parking is available at the Poulton park
 ing lot on Partners Way.The Park Alumni Center: The center's address is 245
 0 Alumni Drive in Raleigh\, and parking there is free.What to bring: Volunt
 eers must wear close-toed shoes. Please bring water in a reusable water bot
 tle so you can stay hydrated. All other materials and supplies\, such as gl
 oves\, will be provided.\n\nIf you have questions about the clean-up effort
 \, send an email to sustainability@ncsu.edu.
DTEND:20260424T160000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022451Z
DTSTART:20260424T140000Z
GEO:35.767879;-78.677586
LOCATION:Lake Raleigh
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:NC State Earth Day Cleanup
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51328310281090
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/nc_state_earth_day_clean_up
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UNC Chapel Hill": "https://calendar.unc.edu/event/data-visualization-for-social-science-research-online"}
X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This course introduces modern visual data exploration and commu
 nication methods to social scientists with limited prior experience. Studen
 ts will learn to effectively present data to diverse audiences across multi
 ple formats. The course utilizes the R programming language\, RStudio devel
 opment environment\, and the tidyverse suite of R packages—with particular 
 emphasis on ggplot2—for data processing and visualization.\n\nStudents will
  develop skills to confidently explore data descriptively\, communicate fin
 dings to both academic and general audiences\, and refine model results for
  presentations and publications. The course emphasizes both clarity and aes
 thetic considerations in data visualization\, while incorporating best prac
 tices for practical\, efficient\, and reproducible workflows. Through a uni
 fied toolset\, students will learn to display visualizations effectively ac
 ross web platforms\, academic papers\, reports\, and presentations. Registr
 ation and fee (refundable for students) are required for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260424T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022132Z
DTSTART:20260424T140000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Data Visualization for Social Science Research (Online)
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51064764722410
URL:https://calendar.unc.edu/event/data-visualization-for-social-science-re
 search-online
END:VEVENT
