BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/daniel-davenport-festival-celebrating-a-revolutionary-war-soldier"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:Mark your calendars for April 25th\, 2025 for the first officia
 l Washington County event in 2026 to commemorate America's 250th anniversar
 y! The America 250 NC Washington County 250th Committee and the Washington 
 County Historical Society at the Daniel Davenport Festival have come togeth
 er to commemorate the lives of Revolutionary War Soldiers.\n\nThere will be
  living history demonstrations\, including ropemaking\, examples of soldier
 s' rations and their equipment\, camp cooking\, and others. Period musician
 s will provide musical performances. Other presentations include medicine d
 uring the American Revolution\, and the Tyrrell County Men who served in th
 e American Revolution\, since Washington County was not officially establis
 hed until 1799.\n\nTours of the main house and its assorted buildings\, whi
 ch illustrate 18th-century life\, including a corn crib\, smokehouse\, and 
 a building for the loom\, have been arranged. The Homestead is on the Natio
 nal Register of Historic Places. It is a rare but fine example of a late 18
 th-century yeoman farmer's dwelling\, and it remains in nearly original con
 dition\, despite the fact that the descendants of Davenport lived in the ho
 use until the mid-1970s without making any modern improvements. A truly uni
 que gem in the region.\n\nThe Sons of the American Revolution are holding a
  recognition and wreath-laying ceremony\, including information about Danie
 l Davenport's six-month service in the NC 5th Regiment and his legacy in Wa
 shington County\, at 2:00 pm. Local school children will sing as part of th
 e ceremony.\n\nPlease note: The celebration festival is free\, but the food
  truck on site is not. In addition\, the Homestead does not have a specific
  address. It is located on Mount Tabor Road in Creswell on the corner of St
 ate Route 1143 and 1146. If coming from the direction of Creswell\, it is o
 n the road to the right after a sharp curve at the Mount Tabor Free Will Ba
 ptist Church. You can also use Google Maps\, Davenport Homestead\, Creswell
 \, NC. It will take you there. Please email Chris Barber with any questions
 .
DTEND:20260425T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260425T140000Z
GEO:35.869828;-76.449986
LOCATION: Daniel Davenport Homestead
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Daniel Davenport Festival - Celebrating a Revolutionary War Soldier
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50578647981038
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/daniel-davenport-festival-celebrating-
 a-revolutionary-war-soldier
END:VEVENT
