BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/story-walk-the-hike-by-alison-farrell"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs
DESCRIPTION:StoryWalk® is simply a book and a walking path combined.  In 20
 07\, Anne Fergusson with the Vermont Department of Health had the idea to c
 ombine literacy and exercise. Teaming up with the Kellog Hubbard Library in
  Montpelier they attached laminated pages from a children’s book onto woode
 n posts.  In the ten years since\, StoryWalks have gone up in all 50 states
  and at least 11 countries. The pages are affixed to metal sign stakes and 
 a trail instantly becomes even more fun for children and book-lovers of all
  ages. StoryWalks® will usually remain up for one-to-two weeks along easy t
 rails about one mile or less. The story featured this time is called "The H
 ike" by Alison Farrell. It will be along our Cypress Point Loop Trail.
DTEND:20260501T040000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260430T120000Z
GEO:35.2024;-78.976116
LOCATION:Carvers Creek State Park – Long Valley Farm Access
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Story Walk- "The hike by: Alison Farrell
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52197401036327
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/story-walk-the-hike-by-alison-farrell
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260430T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260430T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082948826
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
