BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/birding-for-beginners-2/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T093000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20251208T230709Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230709Z
UID:14692-1777708800-1777714200@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Birding for Beginners
DESCRIPTION:Build your bird observation skills on a slow stroll through Duke Gardens with Bella Insignares\, education staff at Duke Gardens\, as you gather a list of different birds that use the Gardens. If you have ever found yourself wondering about the birds that are flying or singing around you\, join us to learn more together as a group. Bring your own binoculars if you have them (not required) and a sense of curiosity. \nFee: $10 per person; free for Duke Gardens members with discount code. \nParking: Parking fees apply. \nLocation:  Onsite at Duke Gardens. Meeting location will be included in a program reminder email sent the week before the program. \nAccessibility: This program is designed for small groups outdoors using fully accessible paths of travel.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/birding-for-beginners-2/
LOCATION:Onsite at Duke Gardens – directions to follow
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/060124_Jordan-Abdur-RaoofShotbyJBot_Naturally-Wild-presents-Birding-for-QTBIPOC_-33-crop.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/making-cordage-with-backyard-plants/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260502T130000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20251208T230703Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230703Z
UID:14694-1777714200-1777726800@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Making Cordage with Backyard Plants
DESCRIPTION:Learn to create strong and beautiful cord from fibers growing in your backyard with Angela Eastman of Flag Mountain Studio. We will cover processing the bast fibers or whole leaves of many plants (such as daffodil\, iris\, daylily\, crocosmia and the inner barks of many vines such as kudzu\, wisteria and more) to create cordage\, an ancient craft practiced around the world. \nFee: $65; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code. \nParking: Parking fees apply. \nLocation: Onsite at Duke Gardens. Meeting location will be included in a program reminder email sent the week before the program. \nAccessibility: This will be a small group program that takes place indoors with available seating.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/making-cordage-with-backyard-plants/
LOCATION:Onsite at Duke Gardens – directions to follow
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/shutterstock_2632152585.jpg
END:VEVENT
