CREATED:20250423T123943Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T193734Z
UID:12335-1778240700-1778246100@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Japanese Tea Gathering: Children’s Day
DESCRIPTION:Join Chizuko Sueyoshi and members of the Japanese Tea Practitioners of Durham for a moment of respite in the Duke Gardens teahouse\, where you will experience the centering calm of a traditional Japanese tea gathering. Enjoy the aesthetics\, poetry and serenity of this rich tradition over an enticing bowl of whisked green tea and a Japanese confection. Guests will meet onsite at Duke Gardens\, to be escorted on a 10-minute walk to the teahouse. Seating is on the ground unless a chair is requested during registration by emailing GardensEducation@duke.edu. Capacity of eight; for ages 12 and up. \nFee: $68; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code \nParking: Parking fees apply. \nLocation: Onsite at Duke Gardens \nAccessibility: This is a small group program that takes place seated on the ground inside a non-climate controlled space. To reach the teahouse\, the group will travel together on a combination of paved and unpaved paths with some uneven surfaces and moderate inclines. Seating is on the ground unless a chair is requested in advance. Email GardensEducation@duke.edu to request a chair.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/may-childrens-day-japanese-tea-gathering/
LOCATION:Onsite at Duke Gardens – directions to follow
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs,Tea Ceremony
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/Tea_Gathering_102023_Amy_Buckalew_0485.jpg
END:VEVENT
