BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/cherry-point-air-show"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:As the nation celebrates 250 years of American independence\, t
 he 2026 show will aim to honor our heritage with a powerful display of airp
 ower\, patriotic unity\, and national pride.\n\n“The MCAS Cherry Point Air 
 Show is more than an aviation event\, it’s a celebration of American excell
 ence and a tribute to the strength\, innovation\, and freedom our nation ha
 s stood for over two and a half centuries\,” said Col. Brendan “Cletus” Bur
 ks\, commanding officer of MCAS Cherry Point. “In partnership with 2nd Mari
 ne Aircraft Wing and our community\, we are proud to host a world-class eve
 nt that reflects the professionalism of our Marines and the enduring bond w
 e share with Eastern North Carolina.”\n\nHeadlining the 2026 event is the r
 eturn of the legendary U.S. Navy Blue Angels\, joined by an exciting lineup
  of military and civilian acts that continue to inspire and captivate. Fan-
 favorite performances such as the jet truck\, parachute jump team\, and aer
 obatic pilots like Randy Ball\, RJ Gritter and Tom Larkin are already slate
 d to return.\n\nAs always\, the air show will be free and open to the publi
 c\, with general admission and parking offered at no cost. Premium seating 
 options will also be available for those seeking upgraded amenities. Visito
 rs can expect an immersive experience filled with aerial demonstrations\, a
 ircraft static displays\, food vendors\, and interactive exhibits for guest
 s of all ages.
DTEND:20260509T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260509T140000Z
GEO:34.883197;-76.905866
LOCATION:Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Cherry Point Air Show
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51276270628841
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/cherry-point-air-show
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/reed-gold-mine-mining-in-society-merit-badge-1640"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Workshops & Trainings
DESCRIPTION:Registered Scouts will have the opportunity to complete all req
 uirements needed to earn the “Mining in Society” merit badge at Reed Gold M
 ine’s merit badge workshop.\n\nThe workshop begins with a PowerPoint presen
 tation and class time to finish the sections of the “Mining in Society” mer
 it badge workbook. After completing the in-class portion\, Scouts will be t
 aken on a guided tour of the underground mine and learn about Reed Gold Min
 e’s history and learn more about the gold mining process. Following that\, 
 weather permitting\, Scouts will be able to pan for gold in the outdoor pan
 ning area.\n\nThere is a $15 registration fee per Scout\, which includes th
 e cost of the workshop\, tour\, and one panning ticket (weather permitting)
 . Adult leaders and chaperones who wish to pan with their Scouts can purcha
 se a panning ticket in the gift shop. Panning tickets are sold on a first c
 ome\, first served basis and are $4.00 after tax. Adult leaders and chapero
 nes may also buy a tour ticket if they’re interested in going on the guided
  tour of the underground mine. Tour tickets are $5.00 for adults 13 and old
 er.\n\nIn 2026\, “Mining in Society” merit badge workshops will be offered 
 May 9\, June 13\, July 11\, August 8\, September 12\, October 10\, and Nove
 mber 14. Each workshop begins at 10:00 am and runs until 2:00 pm and is lim
 ited to 60 participants.\n\nRegistration form- https://tinyurl.com/5ubvkkkc
 \n\nFor more information and to schedule\, contact Reed Gold Mine’s Educati
 on Coordinator\, Logan Stamper. He can be reached by email at logan.stamper
 @dncr.nc.gov or by phone at (704) 721-4653.
DTEND:20260509T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260509T140000Z
GEO:35.285531;-80.466459
LOCATION:Reed Gold Mine
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Reed Gold Mine Mining In Society Merit Badge
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51781977247802
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/reed-gold-mine-mining-in-society-merit
 -badge-1640
END:VEVENT
