BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/the-road-to-yorktown-living-history-day"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:Historic Halifax’s Road to Yorktown explores how North Carolina
 ’s commitment to American Independence as expressed in the April 12th\, 177
 6\, “Halifax Resolves” was challenged with the arrival of the British Army 
 in the spring of 1781. Costumed reenactors\, military camps and historic we
 apons demonstrations bring this period of North Carolina's history to life.
  Free.
DTEND:20260509T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260509T140000Z
GEO:36.329317;-77.588638
