BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/cherry-point-air-show"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:As the nation celebrates 250 years of American independence\, t
 he 2026 show will aim to honor our heritage with a powerful display of airp
 ower\, patriotic unity\, and national pride.\n\n“The MCAS Cherry Point Air 
 Show is more than an aviation event\, it’s a celebration of American excell
 ence and a tribute to the strength\, innovation\, and freedom our nation ha
 s stood for over two and a half centuries\,” said Col. Brendan “Cletus” Bur
 ks\, commanding officer of MCAS Cherry Point. “In partnership with 2nd Mari
 ne Aircraft Wing and our community\, we are proud to host a world-class eve
 nt that reflects the professionalism of our Marines and the enduring bond w
 e share with Eastern North Carolina.”\n\nHeadlining the 2026 event is the r
 eturn of the legendary U.S. Navy Blue Angels\, joined by an exciting lineup
  of military and civilian acts that continue to inspire and captivate. Fan-
 favorite performances such as the jet truck\, parachute jump team\, and aer
 obatic pilots like Randy Ball\, RJ Gritter and Tom Larkin are already slate
 d to return.\n\nAs always\, the air show will be free and open to the publi
 c\, with general admission and parking offered at no cost. Premium seating 
 options will also be available for those seeking upgraded amenities. Visito
 rs can expect an immersive experience filled with aerial demonstrations\, a
 ircraft static displays\, food vendors\, and interactive exhibits for guest
 s of all ages.
DTEND:20260510T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260510T140000Z
GEO:34.883197;-76.905866
LOCATION:Marine Corps Air Station Cherry Point
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Cherry Point Air Show
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51276270629866
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/cherry-point-air-show
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Exhibits & Tours,Exhibitions
DESCRIPTION:March 14 – August 23\, 2026\n\nIn the ultimate battle for survi
 val\, every animal has a plan.\n\nExplore the striking ways nature fights b
 ack in “Staying Alive\,” featuring 17 live animals from around the world wi
 th unbelievable self-defense strategies. Come face to face with trippy toad
 s\, armored armadillos\, a two-toed sloth and more.\n\nDiscover how these d
 efenders deploy an amazing arsenal of high-fashion camouflage and mimicry\,
  specialized armor and advanced chemical warfare – like stink bombs\, caboo
 se cannons and smoke screens – to hide in plain sight\, stand their ground 
 or even drop a limb and make a run for it. Enjoy live animal encounters\, l
 arger-than-life sculptures\, 3D tactile experiences and interactive program
 s.\n\nPerfect for families and animal enthusiasts of all ages. Offered in E
 nglish & Spanish.
DTEND:20260510T210000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260510T140000Z
GEO:35.782156;-78.639336
LOCATION:North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Staying Alive 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52207082959075
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/staying-alive
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/bike-maintenance-class-group-ride"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Every second Sunday\, get your biking fix with the Greenway Gea
 r Collective's Bike Maintenance Class and Group Ride. Their 10 a.m. monthly
  basic maintenance class is a great way to learn the essentials of bike car
 e and tune-ups. Each class is shaped by the needs of those who show up with
  no two being the same.\n\nThen at noon\, you can join a themed group ride 
 starting and ending at The Bike Library container on the shores of Lake Ral
 eigh. Bring your own bike or rent one of theirs. Feel free to show up for t
 he class\, the group ride or both.\n\nWhile both of these events are drop-i
 n accessible and encouraged\, signing up in advance for the class or pre-fi
 lling out the waiver for the ride is always greatly appreciated.
DTEND:20260510T170000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022452Z
DTSTART:20260510T140000Z
GEO:35.767879;-78.677586
LOCATION:Lake Raleigh\, The Bike Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Bike Maintenance Class and Group Ride
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51435730114478
URL:https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/bike-maintenance-class-group-ride
