BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/battle-of-alamance-reenactment-255th-anniversary-commemoration"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:In May 1771\, an armed band of backcountry farmers known as the
  Regulators clashed with Royal Governor William Tryon’s North Carolina mili
 tia on the very ground now preserved as the Alamance Battleground State His
 toric Site. \n\nThis spring\, join us as we honor the 255th anniversary wit
 h a special reenactment and commemoration. Mark your calendars and stay tun
 ed for details on how you can experience history brought vividly to life.
DTEND:20260516T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260516T150000Z
GEO:36.009795;-79.521351
LOCATION:Alamance Battleground State Historic Site
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY: Battle of Alamance Reenactment: 255th Anniversary Commemoration
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51339822153285
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/battle-of-alamance-reenactment-255th-a
 nniversary-commemoration
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/old-hillsborough-road-market-5301"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:James and Nancy Bennett lived along the Hillsborough Road\, a m
 ajor throughway between the county seat of Hillsborough and the state capit
 al of Raleigh. They made money by selling goods & services to passers-by on
  the roadway.\n\nOn May 16\, Bennett Place State Historic Site brings back 
 that entrepreneurial\, small-business spirit with the Old Hillsborough Road
  Market. Shop local craft\, retail\, and food vendors while exploring our h
 istoric site! The program also features historic trades demonstrations and 
 free ranger-talks in the Bennett home.\n\n \n\nVendors wanted! Please conta
 ct us for more information about registration requirements.
DTEND:20260516T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260516T150000Z
GEO:36.029293;-78.975047
LOCATION:Bennett Place State Historic Site
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Old Hillsborough Road Market
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51958156603274
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/old-hillsborough-road-market-5301
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC State University": "https://calendar.ncsu.edu/event/ggc-adventure-series-practice-adventure-race"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ncsu
X-SOURCE:NC State University
CATEGORIES:Community Events
DESCRIPTION:Back for another year of inspiring adventures in nature\, this 
 season of the Greenway Gear Collective Adventure Series will feature Advent
 ure Race themed outings.\nEach event will focus on one of the disciplines o
 f adventure racing: traditionally mountain biking\, orienteering (map and c
 ompass navigation)\, and paddling (canoe or kayak) and will take place at o
 r around Lake Raleigh. Beginners or veterans alike will be in excellent han
 ds with each adventure led by Debra and Jeff Rezeli\, experts with over 11 
 years of adventure racing experience.\nRegister for each event here.\n\nFor
  those who love a goal to build towards...\nThe series will build skills in
  advance of a local practice 3-hour adventure race in May and the option to
  register and participate in a 5-hour adventure race hosted by Broad Run Of
 froad on June 13 & 14 at Lake Anna State Park in Spotsylvania\, VA.\nFor mo
 re information on adventure racing\, check out the US Adventure Racing Asso
 ciation website.
DTEND:20260516T173000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022452Z
DTSTART:20260516T150000Z
GEO:35.767879;-78.677586
LOCATION:Lake Raleigh\, The Bike Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:GGC Adventure Series: Practice Adventure Race
