BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/forest-bathing-walk-4/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260521T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260521T170000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20250711T124736Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230610Z
UID:13400-1779375600-1779382800@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Forest Bathing Walk
DESCRIPTION:Come discover the regenerative power of mindful engagement with nature with certified forest therapy guide Stephanie Campbell. The Japanese tradition of Shinrin-Yoku\, forest bathing\, is a practice using all your senses to connect with nature. Many studies have found it to help decrease stress\, increase immune system functioning and improve concentration\, creativity and mood. In a slow-paced\, two-hour session\, Stephanie will offer a sequence of gentle invitations designed to help you immerse yourself in a deeper connection with nature\, ending with a forest-based tea. \nFee: $32; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code. \nParking: Fees apply. \nLocation: Onsite at Duke Gardens. Meeting location will be included in a program reminder email sent the week before the program. \nAccessibility: This will be a small group program that takes place outdoors and traveling on a combination of paved and unpaved paths with some uneven surfaces and moderate inclines.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/forest-bathing-walk-4/
LOCATION:Onsite at Duke Gardens – directions to follow
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/Bodine_Forest-Bathing_20240510-6374-1.jpg
END:VEVENT
