X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/painting-collections-flowers-in-art/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260523T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260523T113000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20251208T230602Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230602Z
UID:14715-1779530400-1779535800@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Painting Collections: Flowers in Art
DESCRIPTION:Gardens with botanical artist Julia Einstein. Be inspired by botanical still lifes\, floral motifs and natural forms in the decorative arts. You will be guided to “paint” with pencil and use techniques to add color. Take home a folio of your discoveries in a set of watercolors. Julia creates a welcoming\, inclusive environment for artists of all skill levels. All materials are included in the cost. \nFee: $36; 20% discount for Duke Gardens members with discount code \nParking: Fees apply. \nLocation: Onsite at Duke Gardens. Meeting location will be included in a program reminder email sent the week before the program. \nAccessibility: This program will take place seated indoors\, in a location accessible by fully paved paths.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/painting-collections-flowers-in-art/
LOCATION:Onsite at Duke Gardens – directions to follow
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/Growing-2024-Inside-Front-Cover-by-Kathy-Julian.jpg
END:VEVENT
