X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Sarah P. Duke Gardens": "https://gardens.duke.edu/event/native-plant-solutions-fall-forward-perennials/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:duke_gardens
X-SOURCE:Sarah P. Duke Gardens
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260602T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260602T130000
DTSTAMP:20260306T212505
CREATED:20251208T230549Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251208T230549Z
UID:14722-1780401600-1780405200@gardens.duke.edu
SUMMARY:Native Plant Solutions: Fall Forward Perennials
DESCRIPTION:Does your landscape look tired near the end of summer? Give yourself and the wildlife around you a boost with fall-forward perennials. At their peak during late summer and fall\, these species have unique charms and an important ecological role. They give pollinators the resources they need before transitioning to the next stage of development. The superstars of autumn\, asters and goldenrods\, are keystone species that lend outsized support to food webs. They and other fall-forward plants extend the season visually and offer a rich tapestry of color and radiance optimized for the changing angle of the sun. Join Shannon Currey\, education and outreach at Izel Native Plants\, to learn more about lighting up your landscape with fall in mind! \nFee: Free; registration required. \nLocation: Zoom. The recording will be shared with all registrants. \nAccessibility: This will be a virtual program that takes place on Zoom with the option to enable closed captioning.
URL:https://gardens.duke.edu/event/native-plant-solutions-fall-forward-perennials/
LOCATION:Virtual (Zoom)
CATEGORIES:Adult Programs,Virtual Programs
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://gardens.duke.edu/wp-content/uploads/bg-goldenrod-solidago-Hanley_Blomquist_prairie-closeup_9-19-20_p1.jpg
END:VEVENT
