X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/national-trails-day-scavenger-hunt"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Outdoor & Recreation,Outdoor Recreation (kayak, paddle, hikes),E
 ducation Programs,Youth & Family Activities
DESCRIPTION:Get outside for National Trails Day! Meet a ranger at Boone For
 k Parking Area (milepost 299.9 on the Blue Ridge Parkway) and grab a trail 
 scavenger hunt to complete on Nuwati Trail. This 3.0 mile out-and-back easy
  to moderate hike leads to a beautiful view of Storyteller's Rock\, but can
  you find where all the pictures were taken as you hike along? \n\nThis is 
 a self-guided hike\, please wear appropriate hiking shoes and dress for the
  weather.\n\nThere are no bathrooms at Boone Fork Parking Area.
DTEND:20260606T153000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260606T123000Z
LOCATION:Boone Fork Parking Area
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:National Trails Day Scavenger Hunt
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51825354661023
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/national-trails-day-scavenger-hunt
END:VEVENT
