BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ashe-county-america-250th-celebration"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:Come celebrate the 250th anniversary of the founding of the Uni
 ted States on the grounds of the Museum of Ashe County History.\n\nOn this 
 day\, set aside to celebrate\, learn\, and reflect\, visitors will have the
  opportunity to chat with living historians about the American Revolution\,
  see craft demonstrations\, enjoy children's activities\, and listen to his
 toric lectures.\n\nAt 11 a.m. the Daniel Boone Chapter of the Daughters of 
 the American Revolution will read the Declaration of Independence. Later th
 at day\, at 1 p.m.\, historian Michael C. Hardy will give a lecture on his 
 newest book\, "Western North Carolina and Eastern Tennessee and the America
 n Revolution."\n\nVisitors are encouraged to tour the exhibits within the M
 useum of Ashe County History to learn more about their local heritage.\n\nT
 his event is FREE and open to the public.
DTEND:20260606T200000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260606T140000Z
GEO:36.421242;-81.470564
LOCATION:Museum of Ashe County History
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Ashe County America 250th Celebration 
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51958929875802
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/ashe-county-america-250th-celebration
END:VEVENT
