X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/america-250-stars-and-stripes"}
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/america-250-stars-and-stripes"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Performances & Arts,Dance
DESCRIPTION:Wilmington Conservatory’s 2026 performance will take the stage 
 on June 6th at the Wilson Center in Downtown Wilmington. Travel through our
  nations art history this summer.\n\nThe Wilmington Conservatory presents "
 America 250: Stars and Stripes"\, a vibrant mixed repertory showcase celebr
 ating the 250th anniversary of the Declaration of Independence through danc
 e and music. Step right up for a captivating journey through the eras of Am
 erican art\, from early storytelling traditions to the trailblazers who sha
 ped our nation’s artistic heritage\, and discover how history inspires art 
 and how art\, in turn\, shapes history.\n\nExperience iconic works such as 
 Rodeo\, inspired by modern dance pioneer Agnes de Mille and the American fr
 ontier\; Gershwin’s Rhapsody in Blue from the 1920s Jazz Era\; a tribute ho
 noring the U.S. military\; songs from Elvis Presley echoing the spirit of M
 artin Luther King Jr.’s historic speech\; an intertribal showcase featuring
  Native American tribes of the Southeastern United States\; and a grand fin
 ale original ballet of Stars and Stripes Forever\, with music from John Phi
 lip Sousa and Hershey Kay\, inspired by George Balanchine. Plus\, enjoy the
  styles and sounds of Scott Joplin\, Benny Goodman\, Isadora Duncan\, Gus G
 iordano\, Alvin Ailey\, Aretha Franklin\, Gene Kelly\, Judy Garland\, and m
 ore\, brought to life by the dancers of Wilmington Conservatory of Fine Art
 s and guided by original story narration.\n\nAs our nation and community co
 me together to mark this Quarter Millennium\, this moving museum of America
 n art invites audiences to celebrate the creativity legacy of our nation\, 
 honoring 250 years of the United States and the artists who continue to ins
 pire the next generation.
DTEND:20260606T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260606T170000Z
GEO:34.243838;-77.947745
LOCATION:Wilson Center
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:America 250 Stars and Stripes
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52200337317604
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/america-250-stars-and-stripes
END:VEVENT
