X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/flags-of-the-american-revolution"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks
DESCRIPTION:The 250th Anniversary of our great nation is upon us\, and ther
 e are many aspects of our history that we may not know.   For example\, our
  American flag has evolved and changed many times over the years.  Have you
  ever wondered what our very first flag looked like\, and how and why it ch
 anged during the time of our American Revolution?  Members of the New Bern 
 Chapter of the Sons of the American Revolution will display and share some 
 of the exciting history behind our flag\, as well as other interesting info
 rmation\, during their presentation on June 8\, 2026\, at 4:30 pm.  For mor
 e information\, please contact us at 252-566-3772 or at lagrange@neuselibra
 ry.org.
DTEND:20260608T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260608T203000Z
GEO:35.305107;-77.787537
LOCATION:La Grange Public Library
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Flags of the American Revolution
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51843821773945
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/flags-of-the-american-revolution
