X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Triangle Developers": "https://www.meetup.com/triangle-devs/events/qgxhwtyjcjbmb/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_triangle_devs
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Triangle Developers
UID:event_qgxhwtyjcjbmb@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260307T022514Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260609T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260609T200000
SUMMARY:Durham Social Hack Night
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Developers\nHey tech folks\, come out and hang at Hi-
 Wire starting at 6pm! Hack Night is meant to be a social evening for folks
  in tech. It's less about networking and more about community.\n\n**Look f
 or the Hack Night tabletop sign** and nerds wearing name tags to find us. 
 If the weather is nice\, we'll probably be outside.\n\nHelp folks feel wel
 come by using the **"Pac Man Rule"** \\- when standing with a group of peo
 ple \\(usually in a circle\\)\\\, leave some space open so that another pe
 rson can easily join\\.\n\nSee our [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/Tr
 iangleDevsSlack/policies/blob/master/code-of-conduct.md). To summarize: be
  nice or leave. No tolerance for harassment or oppression. In addition\, s
 ince alcohol is present at these events\, please be mindful of your consum
 ption and respect other people's choices on whether or not to consume.\n\n
 **FAQs**\n*Do folks hack at Hack Night? Should I bring my computer?*\nThis
  is more of a night for hackers than an actual hack night. You're welcome 
 to bring a laptop\, but most people will only be socializing.\n\n*What are
  the beverage options? Are there any non-alcoholic drinks?*\nHi-Wire Brewi
 ng offers many types of beers including a few non-alcoholic options plus w
 ine and some liquor. They usually have a happy hour special on the first f
 ew beers on the menu. In the same complex are Cugino Forno which has addit
 ional drink options\, and Two Roosters which has excellent ice cream.\n\n*
 Are there any drink specials?*\nIf Hack Night is on a Tuesday\, Hi-Wire us
 ually has $5 pints for their flagship beers. Look for the list at the coun
 ter.\n\n*Do people eat snacks/dinner during the meetup?*\nSometimes folks 
 will order a pizza or salad from Cugino Forno. I sometimes grab an ice cre
 am from Two Roosters across the way. Most people eat before or after but i
 t's no big deal - whatever you prefer and are most comfortable with.\n\n*H
 ow can I connect with the developer community?*\nGo to [triangledevelopers
 .com](https://triangledevelopers.com/) to find the Discord and Slack info.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/triangle-devs/events/qgxhwtyjcjbmb/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260304T180814Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T180814Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
