X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Education Programs,Lectures & Talks,Celebrations & Commemoration
 s,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:"A man's rights rest in three boxes. The ballot box\, jury box 
 and the cartridge box. Let no man be kept from the ballot box because of hi
 s color. Let no woman be kept from the ballot box..." -Frederick Douglass\,
  November 15th\, 1867.\n\n\nJoin us in June for an exploration of voting ri
 ghts in North Carolina and a deeper examination of the relationship between
  violence and political participation.
DTEND:20260620T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260620T140000Z
GEO:35.520185;-77.976051
LOCATION:Governor Charles B. Aycock Birthplace
