BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/nc-4th-of-july-festival"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Festivals & Fairs
DESCRIPTION:2026 NC 4th of July Festival: Celebrating 250 Years of Independ
 ence\nJune 28 – July 4\, 2026 | Southport\, North Carolina\n\nJoin us in hi
 storic Southport for one of North Carolina’s most beloved traditions\, the 
 NC 4th of July Festival. In 2026\, the celebration takes on even greater me
 aning as we honor the 250th anniversary of American independence\, part of 
 the nationwide America250 Semiquincentennial.\n\nFor over two centuries\, c
 ommunities across North Carolina have gathered to mark our nation’s birthda
 y. This year\, from June 28 through July 4\, the NC 4th of July Festival wi
 ll bring together visitors for a week of parades\, concerts\, arts and craf
 ts\, family activities\, and patriotic ceremonies\, all infused with the sp
 irit of America’s 250th birthday.\n\nFestival Highlights\n\nGrand Parade fe
 aturing floats\, marching bands\, and community groups decked out in patrio
 tic spirit\n\nLive Music & Entertainment on multiple stages\, showcasing di
 verse voices and talents from across the region\n\nFireworks Over the Water
  — a breathtaking tradition made even more meaningful in this Semiquincente
 nnial year\n\nArts\, Crafts & Food Vendors with local flavors and handmade 
 treasures\n\nFamily Activities\, including games\, educational exhibits\, a
 nd history-themed programming inspired by America250\n\nCommemorative Progr
 ams highlighting North Carolina’s role in the American story\, from 1776 to
  today\n\nAmerica250 Connection\n\nAs part of the America250 NC initiative\
 , this year’s festival will not only celebrate our nation’s founding ideals
  — liberty\, democracy\, and unity — but also spotlight the diverse stories
  that make up our shared history. Through special exhibits\, performances\,
  and community programs\, festival-goers will be invited to reflect on the 
 past\, celebrate the present\, and imagine the next 250 years together.\n\n
 Why 2026 is Special\n\nThis year’s festival isn’t just a tradition\; it’s p
 art of a once-in-a-generation national celebration. By joining us in Southp
 ort\, you’ll be part of history\, experiencing one of the largest and most 
 vibrant Independence Day events in North Carolina during America’s Semiquin
 centennial.
DTEND:20260628T180000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022459Z
DTSTART:20260628T170000Z
GEO:33.916757;-78.018647
LOCATION:Southport Waterfront Park 
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:NC 4th of July Festival
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50754361378770
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/nc-4th-of-july-festival
END:VEVENT
