BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/independence-comes-to-nc"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Ceremonies & Anniversaries
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that North Carolina’s first public reading of the 
 Declaration of Independence took place in Halifax on August 1st\, 1776?  Jo
 in historical interpreters as they reenact events surrounding the joyous ne
 ws of American independence from Britain. At 12:00pm\, see a reenactor port
 ray Cornelius Harnett\, President of the Council of Safety\, read the Decla
 ration for the first time in North Carolina. View a screening of The Americ
 an Constitution\, a new documentary film on the writing of the United State
 s Constitution\, which was partially filmed at Historic Halifax. Free.
DTEND:20260801T220000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022500Z
DTSTART:20260801T140000Z
GEO:36.329317;-77.588638
LOCATION:Historic Halifax
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Independence Comes to NC!
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51586147425438
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/independence-comes-to-nc
END:VEVENT
