X-SOURCE-ID:unc_chapel_hill
X-SOURCE:UNC Chapel Hill
CATEGORIES:Workshops and Classes
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour course introduces learners to the foundations of su
 rvey development for primary data collection. Students will learn fundament
 al practices in planning\, designing\, and conducting data collection using
  survey research best practices. Core topics will cover:\n\nsampling and ou
 treachquestionnaire development (writing questions\, response options\, and
  question ordering)visual design considerations of electronic and paper sur
 veysapproaches for testing\, and monitoringParticipants will have the oppor
 tunity to draft and review survey questions\, explore resources for existin
 g survey questions\, and review the strengths and limitations of various da
 ta collection modes.\n\nRegistration and fee (refundable for students) are 
 required for Zoom link access.
DTEND:20260929T190000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022132Z
DTSTART:20260929T170000Z
LOCATION:
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:Introduction to Survey Development (Online)
