END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"NC Cultural Resources": "https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/an-18th-century-christmas"}
X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:Join us once again this holiday season\, as we explore how the 
 American colonists celebrated Christmas. During the program\, you can enjoy
  18th-century-inspired refreshments in the Visitor Center\, participate in 
 traditional games\, or try your hand at Moravian paper stars and other 18th
 -century crafts. The highlight of the evening will be an authentic\nperiod 
 candlelit service in the ruins of St. Philip's Anglican Church. The service
  will begin at 5:00pm and will conclude by 5:30pm. Tickets can be purchased
  at the gate on the day of.\n$5 per person.
DTEND:20261213T223000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022500Z
DTSTART:20261213T180000Z
GEO:34.040206;-77.946023
LOCATION:Brunswick Town/Fort Anderson
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:An 18th Century Christmas
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_51851019111989
URL:https://events.dncr.nc.gov/event/an-18th-century-christmas
END:VEVENT
