X-SOURCE-ID:nc_cultural_resources
X-SOURCE:NC Cultural Resources
CATEGORIES:Celebrations & Commemorations,Reenactments & Living History
DESCRIPTION:Prepare to celebrate and enjoy festive Scottish traditions for 
 New Year’s Eve (Hogmanay) and the Yule season. Enjoy speaking to Revolution
 ary soldiers of the NC Highland and 71st Regiments\, listen to Gaelic music
  and storytelling\, learn about tartan history and see traditional Hogmanay
  dishes made over an open fire\, and more. We encourage you to dress in you
 r family tartan or plaid! Food not available to the public. FREE. All ages 
 welcome. Drop-in.
DTEND:20261219T213000Z
DTSTAMP:20260307T022500Z
DTSTART:20261219T150000Z
GEO:35.979741;-79.992174
LOCATION:High Point Museum
